tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\\" width=\\\"8.859ex\\\" height=\\\"2.163ex\\\" role=\\\"img\\\" focusable=\\\"false\\\" viewBox=\\\"0 -750 3915.7 956\\\" xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" style=\\\"vertical-align: -0.466ex;\\\"><defs><path id=\\\"MJX-3-TEX-N-34\\\" d=\\\"M462 0Q444 3 333 3Q217 3 199 0H190V46H221Q241 46 248 46T265 48T279 53T286 61Q287 63 287 115V165H28V211L179 442Q332 674 334 675Q336 677 355 677H373L379 671V211H471V165H379V114Q379 73 379 66T385 54Q393 47 442 46H471V0H462ZM293 211V545L74 212L183 211H293Z\\\"></path><path id=\\\"MJX-3-TEX-N-6B\\\" d=\\\"M36 46H50Q89 46 97 60V68Q97 77 97 91T97 124T98 167T98 217T98 272T98 329Q98 366 98 407T98 482T98 542T97 586T97 603Q94 622 83 628T38 637H20V660Q20 683 22 683L32 684Q42 685 61 686T98 688Q115 689 135 690T165 693T176 694H179V463L180 233L240 287Q300 341 304 347Q310 356 310 364Q310 383 289 385H284V431H293Q308 428 412 428Q475 428 484 431H489V385H476Q407 380 360 341Q286 278 286 274Q286 273 349 181T420 79Q434 60 451 53T500 46H511V0H505Q496 3 418 3Q3\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/1000/image/6y3zli1mlnc7w4c/043f1baa-b9aa-42a2-b49a-64c36e2eb419/c284a9c0-0a33-11f1-bd6f-a77e3b4a8273/file-6y3zli1mlnc7w4d.webp?format=webp\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pin-the-given-figure-the-blocks-a-b-and-c-weigh-4-m-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-t3z9u8iplgwprvv3\"},{\"i\":5,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Three blocks $$\\\\mathrm{M_1, M_2, M_3}$$ having masses $$4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, 6 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ respectively are hanging from a smooth pully using rope 1, 2 and 3 as shown in figure. The tension in the rope $$\\\\mathrm{1, T_1}$$ when they are moving upward with acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$ is __________ $$\\\\mathrm{N}$$ (if $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$).\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">3</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Three blocks $$\\\\mathrm{M_1, M_2, M_3}$$ having masses $$4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, 6 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ respectively are hanging from a smooth pully using rope 1, 2 and 3 as shown in figure. The tension in the rope $$\\\\mathrm{1, T_1}$$ when they are moving upward with acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$ is __________ $$\\\\mathrm{N}$$ (if $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$).</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lv7liksj/3c27e0a1-15d8-470b-8909-546e58175912/f396a130-fecd-11ee-8116-e195dc03b165/file-1lv7liksk.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lv7liksj/3c27e0a1-15d8-470b-8909-546e58175912/f396a130-fecd-11ee-8116-e195dc03b165/file-1lv7liksk.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 25 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lv7liksj/3c27e0a1-15d8-470b-8909-546e58175912/f396a130-fecd-11ee-8116-e195dc03b165/file-1lv7liksk.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthree-blocks-mathrmm1-m2-m3-having-masses-4-jee-main-physics-motion-s5inhklf6lkhqvkn\"},{\"i\":6,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Two forces $$\\\\overline{\\\\mathrm{F}}_1$$ and $$\\\\overline{\\\\mathrm{F}}_2$$ are acting on a body. One force has magnitude thrice that of the other force and the resultant of the two forces is equal to the force of larger magnitude. The angle between $$\\\\vec{F}_1$$ and $$\\\\vec{F}_2$$ is $$\\\\cos ^{-1}\\\\left(\\\\frac{1}{n}\\\\right)$$. The value of $$|n|$$ is _______.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">4</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Two forces $$\\\\overline{\\\\mathrm{F}}_1$$ and $$\\\\overline{\\\\mathrm{F}}_2$$ are acting on a body. One force has magnitude thrice that of the other force and the resultant of the two forces is equal to the force of larger magnitude. The angle between $$\\\\vec{F}_1$$ and $$\\\\vec{F}_2$$ is $$\\\\cos ^{-1}\\\\left(\\\\frac{1}{n}\\\\right)$$. The value of $$|n|$$ is _______.</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 4th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/ptwo-forces-overlinemathrmf1-and-overlinem-jee-main-physics-motion-uqbwhqrihs401thx\"},{\"i\":7,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Two inclined planes are placed as shown in figure. A block is projected from the Point A of inclined plane AB along its surface with a velocity just sufficient to carry it to the top Point B at a height 10 m. After reaching the Point B the block slides down on inclined plane BC. Time it takes to reach to the point C from point A is $$t(\\\\sqrt{2}+1)$$ s. The value of t is ___________. (use $$\\\\mathrm{~g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$ )\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">5</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Two inclined planes are placed as shown in figure. A block is projected from the Point A of inclined plane AB along its surface with a velocity just sufficient to carry it to the top Point B at a height 10 m. After reaching the Point B the block slides down on inclined plane BC. Time it takes to reach to the point C from point A is $$t(\\\\sqrt{2}+1)$$ s. The value of t is ___________.</p>\\n<p>(use $$\\\\mathrm{~g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$ )</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6qqj3m7/b243ae4b-6c83-447d-b6da-4b558c5f5ad3/0ba439f0-1a63-11ed-9fca-fdfa82878a71/file-1l6qqj3m8.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6qqj3m7/b243ae4b-6c83-447d-b6da-4b558c5f5ad3/0ba439f0-1a63-11ed-9fca-fdfa82878a71/file-1l6qqj3m8.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th July Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 63 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6qqj3m7/b243ae4b-6c83-447d-b6da-4b558c5f5ad3/0ba439f0-1a63-11ed-9fca-fdfa82878a71/file-1l6qqj3m8.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/ptwo-inclined-planes-are-placed-as-shown-in-figure-a-bloc-jee-main-physics-motion-hkp9shnkc6mfxh10\"},{\"i\":8,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Four forces are acting at a point $$\\\\mathrm{P}$$ in equilibrium as shown in figure. The ratio of force $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{1}$$ to $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{2}$$ is $$1: x$$ where $$x=$$ _____________. ForceDynamics Simulator\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\