w !important; -webkit-font-smoothing: auto !important; grid: none !important; grid-area: auto !important; hyphens: manual !important; hyphenate-character: auto !important; -webkit-line-break: auto !important; -webkit-line-clamp: none !important; -webkit-locale: auto !important; -webkit-mask-box-image-source: none !important; -webkit-mask-box-image-slice: 0 fill !impo\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5bqm5xe/78cfc10e-145a-479e-9cb8-b8129924e6b6/67bbe620-fe57-11ec-b169-b5046c590266/file-1l5bqm5xf.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-200-g-is-kept-stationary-on-a-smooth-incl-jee-main-physics-motion-k7itwashbdnxywbu\"},{\"i\":13,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A force on an object of mass 100 g is $$\\\\left( {10\\\\widehat i + 5\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$ N. The position of that object at t = 2 s is $$\\\\left( {a\\\\widehat i + b\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$ m after starting from rest. The value of $${a \\\\over b}$$ will be ___________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">11</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A force on an object of mass 100 g is $$\\\\left( {10\\\\widehat i + 5\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$ N. The position of that object at t = 2 s is $$\\\\left( {a\\\\widehat i + b\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$ m after starting from rest. The value of $${a \\\\over b}$$ will be ___________.</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 25th June Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-force-on-an-object-of-mass-100-g-is-left-10wideha-jee-main-physics-motion-hzctnalbxsh07go4\"},{\"i\":14,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"When a body slides down from rest along a smooth inclined plane making an angle of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ with the horizontal, it takes time T. When the same body slides down from the rest along a rough inclined plane making the same angle and through the same distance, it takes time $$\\\\alpha$$T, where $$\\\\alpha$$ is a constant greater than 1. The co-efficient of friction between the body and the rough plane is $${1 \\\\over {\\\\sqrt x }}\\\\left( {{{{\\\\alpha ^2} - 1} \\\\over {{\\\\alpha ^2}}}} \\\\right)$$ where x = __________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">12</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">When a body slides down from rest along a smooth inclined plane making an angle of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ with the horizontal, it takes time T. When the same body slides down from the rest along a rough inclined plane making the same angle and through the same distance, it takes time $$\\\\alpha$$T, where $$\\\\alpha$$ is a constant greater than 1. The co-efficient of friction between the body and the rough plane is $${1 \\\\over {\\\\sqrt x }}\\\\left( {{{{\\\\alpha ^2} - 1} \\\\over {{\\\\alpha ^2}}}} \\\\right)$$ where x = __________.</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 1st September Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/when-a-body-slides-down-from-rest-along-a-smooth-inclined-pl-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-5asegnfevgdck4i3\"},{\"i\":15,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A car is moving on a plane inclined at 30$$^\\\\circ$$ to the horizontal with an acceleration of 10 ms$$-$$2 parallel to the plane upward. A bob is suspended by a string from the roof of the car. The angle in degrees which the string makes with the vertical is ______________. (Take g = 10 ms$$-$$2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">13</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A car is moving on a plane inclined at 30$$^\\\\circ$$ to the horizontal with an acceleration of 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup> parallel to the plane upward. A bob is suspended by a string from the roof of the car. The angle in degrees which the string makes with the vertical is ______________. (Take g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>)</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 31st August Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-car-is-moving-on-a-plane-inclined-at-30circ-to-the-h-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-tombabqti9zwluuo\"},{\"i\":16,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"The coefficient of static friction between two blocks is 0.5 and the table is smooth. The maximum horizontal force that can be applied to move the blocks together is .................. N. (take g = 10 ms-2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">14</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">The coefficient of static friction between two blocks is 0.5 and the table is smooth. The maximum horizontal force that can be applied to move the blocks together is .................. N. (take g = 10 ms<sup>-2</sup>)<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kten36yn/d691372d-c3a1-48f3-8679-ac93454d2db1/5e2c68f0-125d-11ec-a4fb-5347f21481c0/file-1kten36yo.jpeg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 92 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kten36yn/d691372d-c3a1-48f3-8679-ac93454d2db1/5e2c68f0-125d-11ec-a4fb-5347f21481c0/file-1kten36yo.jpeg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/the-coefficient-of-static-friction-between-two-blocks-is-05-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-7bhwf4qmervepg4w\"},{\"i\":17,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass 'm' is launched up on a rough inclined plane making an angle of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ with the horizontal. The coefficient of friction between the body and plane is $${{\\\\sqrt x } \\\\over 5}$$ if the time of ascent is half of the time of descent. The value of x is __________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">15</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A body of mass 'm' is launched up on a rough inclined plane making an angle of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ with the horizontal. The coefficient of friction between the body and plane is $${{\\\\sqrt x } \\\\over 5}$$ if the time of ascent is half of the time of descent. The value of x is __________.</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-body-of-mass-m-is-launched-up-on-a-rough-inclined-plane-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-vpg5pvasbgsuykm4\"},{\"i\":18,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A bullet of mass 0.1 kg is fired on a wooden block to pierce through it, but it stops after moving a distance of 50 cm into it. If the velocity of bullet before hitting the wood is 10 m/s and it slows down with uniform deceleration, then the magnitude of effective retarding force on the bullet is 'x' N. The value of 'x' to the nearest integer is __________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">16</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A bullet of mass 0.1 kg is fired on a wooden block to pierce through it, but it stops after moving a distance of 50 cm into it. If the velocity of bullet before hitting the wood is 10 m/s and it slows down with uniform deceleration, then the magnitude of effective retarding force on the bullet is 'x' N. The value of 'x' to the nearest integer is __________.</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 18th March Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-bullet-of-mass-01-kg-is-fired-on-a-wooden-block-to-pierce-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-kby8wgkat6zck7kf\"},{\"i\":19,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A boy of mass 4 kg is standing on a piece of wood having mass 5 kg. If the coefficient of friction between the wood and the floor is 0.5, the maximum force that the boy can exert on the rope so that the piece of wood does not move from its place is __________ N. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g = 10 ms-2 ]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">17</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A boy of mass 4 kg is standing on a piece of wood having mass 5 kg. If the coefficient of friction between the wood and the floor is 0.5, the maximum force that the boy can exert on the rope so that the piece of wood does not move from its place is __________ N. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g = 10 ms<sup>-2</sup> ]<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmlirnsv/7b168482-d0c1-4fcc-ba95-25f514ab7af8/71d94cf0-8b90-11eb-8bc4-81bde7104d98/file-1kmlirnsw.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 99 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmlirnsv/7b168482-d0c1-4fcc-ba95-25f514ab7af8/71d94cf0-8b90-11eb-8bc4-81bde7104d98/file-1kmlirnsw.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-boy-of-mass-4-kg-is-standing-on-a-piece-of-wood-having-mas-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-lgrdm6ljn9xgtiat\"},{\"i\":20,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass 1 kg rests on a horizontal floor with which it has a coefficient of static friction $${1 \\\\over {\\\\sqrt 3 }}$$. It is desired to make the body move by applying the minimum possible force F N. The value of F will be ____________. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g = 10 ms$$-$$2 ]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">18</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A body of mass 1 kg rests on a horizontal floor with which it has a coefficient of static friction $${1 \\\\over {\\\\sqrt 3 }}$$. It is desired to make the body move by applying the minimum possible force F N. The value of F will be ____________. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup> ]</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-body-of-mass-1-kg-rests-on-a-horizontal-floor-with-which-i-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-wnznoco1zamaj1nw\"},{\"i\":21,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Two blocks (m = 0.5 kg and M = 4.5 kg) are arranged on a horizontal frictionless table as shown in figure. The coefficient of static friction between the two blocks is $${3 \\\\over 7}$$. Then the maximum horizontal force that can be applied on the larger block so that the blocks move together is ___________ N. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g as 9.8 ms$$-$$2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">19</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two blocks (m = 0.5 kg and M = 4.5 kg) are arranged on a horizontal frictionless table as shown in figure. The coefficient of static friction between the two blocks is $${3 \\\\over 7}$$. Then the maximum horizontal force that can be applied on the larger block so that the blocks move together is ___________ N. (Round off to the Nearest Integer) [Take g as 9.8 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>]<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmk2xn2b/2ba05dae-0057-4b68-8a9f-ac118422b82c/bd6b0530-8ac5-11eb-a550-a93c57882a34/file-1kmk2xn2c.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 101 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmk2xn2b/2ba05dae-0057-4b68-8a9f-ac118422b82c/bd6b0530-8ac5-11eb-a550-a93c57882a34/file-1kmk2xn2c.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-blocks-m--05-kg-and-m--45-kg-are-arranged-on-a-hor-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-dpmijbjz7mx5ff7t\"},{\"i\":22,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass 2 kg moves under a force of $$\\\\left( {2\\\\widehat i + 3\\\\widehat j + 5\\\\widehat k} \\\\right)$$N. It starts from rest and was at the origin initially. After 4s, its new coordinates are (8, b, 20). The value of b is _____________. (Round off to the Nearest Integer)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">20</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A body of mass 2 kg moves under a force of $$\\\\left( {2\\\\widehat i + 3\\\\widehat j + 5\\\\widehat k} \\\\right)$$N. It starts from rest and was at the origin initially. After 4s, its new coordinates are (8, b, 20). The value of b is _____________. (Round off to the Nearest Integer)</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 16th March Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-body-of-mass-2-kg-moves-under-a-force-of-left-2wideh-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-zgiqyzsobf0cmpb6\"},{\"i\":23,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A person standing on a spring balance inside a stationary lift measures 60 kg. The weight of that person if the lift descends with uniform downward acceleration of 1.8 m/s2 will be ______________ N. [g = 10 m/s2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">21</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A person standing on a spring balance inside a stationary lift measures 60 kg. The weight of that person if the lift descends with uniform downward acceleration of 1.8 m/s<sup>2</sup> will be ______________ N. [g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>]</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-person-standing-on-a-spring-balance-inside-a-stationary-li-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-imamm5qgabxrwacy\"},{\"i\":24,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A boy pushes a box of mass 2 kg with a force $$\\\\overrightarrow F = \\\\left( {20\\\\widehat i + 10\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)N$$ on a frictionless surface. If the box was initially at rest, then ___________ m is displacement along the x-axis after 10s.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">22</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A boy pushes a box of mass 2 kg with a force $$\\\\overrightarrow F  = \\\\left( {20\\\\widehat i + 10\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)N$$ on a frictionless surface. If the box was initially at rest, then ___________ m is displacement along the x-axis after 10s.</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-boy-pushes-a-box-of-mass-2-kg-with-a-force-overrightarr-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-7zubviwfdo95aehr\"},{\"i\":25,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"As shown in the figure, a block of mass $$\\\\sqrt 3 $$ kg is kept on a horizontal rough surface of coefficient of friction $${1 \\\\over {3\\\\sqrt 3 }}$$. The critical force to be applied on the vertical surface as shown at an angle 60$$^\\\\circ$$ with horizontal such that it does not move, will be 3x. The value of x will be _________. [g = 10 m/s2; sin60$$^\\\\circ$$ = $${{\\\\sqrt 3 } \\\\over 2}$$; cos60$$^\\\\circ$$ = $${1 \\\\over 2}$$]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">23</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">As shown in the figure, a block of mass $$\\\\sqrt 3 $$ kg is kept on a horizontal rough surface of coefficient of friction $${1 \\\\over {3\\\\sqrt 3 }}$$. The critical force to be applied on the vertical surface as shown at an angle 60$$^\\\\circ$$ with horizontal such that it does not move, will be 3x. The value of x will be _________.<br><br> [g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>; sin60$$^\\\\circ$$ = $${{\\\\sqrt 3 } \\\\over 2}$$; cos60$$^\\\\circ$$ = $${1 \\\\over 2}$$]<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kltqspyp/8349ba56-4d81-4998-bf71-1321e98f4eb0/e62d7e10-7c49-11eb-98b4-b931446ae6e4/file-1kltqspyq-279w.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 105 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kltqspyp/8349ba56-4d81-4998-bf71-1321e98f4eb0/e62d7e10-7c49-11eb-98b4-b931446ae6e4/file-1kltqspyq-279w.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/as-shown-in-the-figure-a-block-of-mass-sqrt-3--kg-is-k-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-kilflbwjbgceg1ft\"},{\"i\":26,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"An inclined plane is bent in such a way that the vertical cross-section is given by $$y = {{{x^2}} \\\\over 4}$$ where y is in vertical and x in horizontal direction. If the upper surface of this curved plane is rough with coefficient of friction $$\\\\mu$$ = 0.5, the maximum height in cm at which a stationary block will not slip downward is _________ cm.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">24</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">An inclined plane is bent in such a way that the vertical cross-section is given by $$y = {{{x^2}} \\\\over 4}$$ where y is in vertical and x in horizontal direction. If the upper surface of this curved plane is rough with coefficient of friction $$\\\\mu$$ = 0.5, the maximum height in cm at which a stationary block will not slip downward is _________ cm.</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 24th February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/an-inclined-plane-is-bent-in-such-a-way-that-the-vertical-cr-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-dtjgxvhkreshkseh\"},{\"i\":27,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"The coefficient of static friction between a wooden block of mass 0.5 kg and a vertical rough wall is 0.2. The magnitude of horizontal force that should be applied on the block to keep it adhere to the wall will be _________ N. [g = 10 ms$$-$$2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">25</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">The coefficient of static friction between a wooden block of mass 0.5 kg and a vertical rough wall is 0.2. The magnitude of horizontal force that should be applied on the block to keep it adhere to the wall will be _________ N. [g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>]</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 24th February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/the-coefficient-of-static-friction-between-a-wooden-block-of-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-41dgc5g6f5di8bfv\"},{\"i\":28,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Two blocks ( $P$ and $Q$ ) with respectively masses 2 kg and 1.5 kg are joined by a massless thread. These blocks are mounted on a frictionless pully which is fixed on the edge of a cube $(S)$, as shown in the figure below. Block $P$ is positioned on the top surface which has no friction and block $Q$ is in contact with side-surface, having coefficient friction $\\\\mu$. The cube ( $S$ ) moves towards the right with acceleration of $\\\\frac{g}{2}$, where $g$ is gravitational acceleration. During this movement the block $P$ and $Q$ remain stationary. The value of $\\\\mu$ is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ (take $\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$ )\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">1</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Two blocks ( $P$ and $Q$ ) with respectively masses 2 kg and 1.5 kg are joined by a massless thread. These blocks are mounted on a frictionless pully which is fixed on the edge of a cube $(S)$, as shown in the figure below. Block $P$ is positioned on the top surface which has no friction and block $Q$ is in contact with side-surface, having coefficient friction $\\\\mu$. The cube ( $S$ ) moves towards the right with acceleration of $\\\\frac{g}{2}$, where $g$ is gravitational acceleration. During this movement the block $P$ and $Q$ remain stationary. The value of $\\\\mu$ is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ (take $\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$ )</p>\\n<img alt=\\\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 1 English\\\" src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mo4kt6yz/6e3b6eb2-ba0b-4763-ac72-a65aa06f6daf/1db935b0-3b47-11f1-a2ba-f57fd97b4b05/file-6y3zli1mo4kt6z0.webp?format=webp\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mo4kt6yz/6e3b6eb2-ba0b-4763-ac72-a65aa06f6daf/1db935b0-3b47-11f1-a2ba-f57fd97b4b05/file-6y3zli1mo4kt6z0.webp\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mo4kt6yz/6e3b6eb2-ba0b-4763-ac72-a65aa06f6daf/1db935b0-3b47-11f1-a2ba-f57fd97b4b05/file-6y3zli1mo4kt6z0.webp?format=webp\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/ptwo-blocks--p-and-q--with-respectively-masses-2-kg-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-ts0xvd1id3chnpmx\"},{\"i\":29,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Three masses $m_1=4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, m_2=4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ and $m_3=6 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ are suspended from a fixed smooth frictionless pully as shown in the figure below. The value of $T_1 / T_2$ is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ (take $g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$ )\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">2</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Three masses $m_1=4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, m_2=4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ and $m_3=6 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ are suspended from a fixed smooth frictionless pully as shown in the figure below. The value of $T_1 / T_2$ is</p>\\n<p>$\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$</p>\\n<p>(take $g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$ )</p><img alt=\\\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 2 English\\\" src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mobknnnc/626f6bc5-8336-41c1-8779-78bc3cec9afc/004bff80-3f20-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobknnnd.webp?format=webp\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mobknnnc/626f6bc5-8336-41c1-8779-78bc3cec9afc/004bff80-3f20-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobknnnd.webp\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mobknnnc/626f6bc5-8336-41c1-8779-78bc3cec9afc/004bff80-3f20-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobknnnd.webp?format=webp\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthree-masses-m14-mathrmkg-m24-mathrmkg-and-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-nksqqdst3lyvbseh\"},{\"i\":30,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A wedge $Y$ with mass of 10 kg and all frictionless surfaces and the inclined surface making $37^{\\\\circ}$ with horizontal. A block $X$ with mass 2 kg is placed at the highest point of the wedge as shown in figure is at rest. At $t=0$ wedge ( $Y$ ) is pulled toward right with constant force $(f)$ of 24 N . Taking the block $X$ at rest at $t=0$, the time taken by it to slide down 8.8 m on the slope, while $Y$ is on the move, is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ s. $\\\\left(\\\\right.$ take $\\\\tan \\\\left(37^{\\\\circ}\\\\right)=3 / 4$ and $\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right)$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">3</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A wedge $Y$ with mass of 10 kg and all frictionless surfaces and the inclined surface making $37^{\\\\circ}$ with horizontal. A block $X$ with mass 2 kg is placed at the highest point of the wedge as shown in figure is at rest. At $t=0$ wedge ( $Y$ ) is pulled toward right with constant force $(f)$ of 24 N . Taking the block $X$ at rest at $t=0$, the time taken by it to slide down 8.8 m on the slope, while $Y$ is on the move, is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ s.</p>\\n<p>$\\\\left(\\\\right.$ take $\\\\tan \\\\left(37^{\\\\circ}\\\\right)=3 / 4$ and $\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right)$</p><img alt=\\\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 3 English\\\" src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mobld03y/9ef4ad1b-43d9-45dc-9140-d2c9862cc25b/c126cee0-3f22-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobld03z.webp?format=webp\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mobld03y/9ef4ad1b-43d9-45dc-9140-d2c9862cc25b/c126cee0-3f22-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobld03z.webp\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mobld03y/9ef4ad1b-43d9-45dc-9140-d2c9862cc25b/c126cee0-3f22-11f1-9916-55ae99d96892/file-6y3zli1mobld03z.webp?format=webp\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-wedge-y-with-mass-of-10-kg-and-all-frictionless-surfa-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-gvo4xnsuem0slxhh\"},{\"i\":31,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"The time taken by a block of mass $m$ to slide down from the highest point to the lowest point on a rough inclined plane is $50 \\\\%$ more compared to the time taken by the same block on identical inclined smooth plane. Both inclined planes are at $45^{\\\\circ}$ with the horizontal. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the rough inclined surface and block is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">4</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>The time taken by a block of mass $m$ to slide down from the highest point to the lowest point on a rough inclined plane is $50 \\\\%$ more compared to the time taken by the same block on identical inclined smooth plane. Both inclined planes are at $45^{\\\\circ}$ with the horizontal. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the rough inclined surface and block is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$</p>\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 4th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthe-time-taken-by-a-block-of-mass-m-to-slide-down-from-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-ayauvho2qbsyy2sn\"},{\"i\":32,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A small block of mass m slides down from the top of a frictionless inclined surface, while the inclined plane is moving towards left with constant acceleration $a_0$. The angle between the inclined plane and ground is $\\\\theta$ and its base length is $L$. Assuming that initially the small block is at the top of the inclined plane, the time it takes to reach the lowest point of the inclined plane is ________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">5</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A small block of mass <b>m</b> slides down from the top of a frictionless inclined surface, while the inclined plane is moving towards left with constant acceleration $a_0$. The angle between the inclined plane and ground is $\\\\theta$ and its base length is $L$. Assuming that initially the small block is at the top of the inclined plane, the time it takes to reach the lowest point of the inclined plane is ________.</p>\\n<img alt=\\\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 12 English\\\" src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlbxffqv/ffdaa20a-958f-4433-b4bb-031166eabfd2/4c430870-03ed-11f1-a285-8fe590341dac/file-6y3zli1mlbxffqw.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlbxffqv/ffdaa20a-958f-4433-b4bb-031166eabfd2/4c430870-03ed-11f1-a285-8fe590341dac/file-6y3zli1mlbxffqw.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlbxffqv/ffdaa20a-958f-4433-b4bb-031166eabfd2/4c430870-03ed-11f1-a285-8fe590341dac/file-6y3zli1mlbxffqw.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-small-block-of-mass-bmb-slides-down-from-the-top-o-jee-main-physics-dulpav9wnm9d8eir\"},{\"i\":33,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 5 kg is moving on an inclined plane which makes an angle of $30^{\\\\circ}$ with the horizontal. Friction coefficient between the block and inclined plane surface is $\\\\frac{\\\\sqrt{3}}{2}$. The force to be applied on the block so that the block will move down without acceleration is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ N. $$ \\\\left(g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right) . $$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">6</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass 5 kg is moving on an inclined plane which makes an angle of $30^{\\\\circ}$ with the horizontal. Friction coefficient between the block and inclined plane surface is $\\\\frac{\\\\sqrt{3}}{2}$. The force to be applied on the block so that the block will move down without acceleration is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ N.</p>\\n<p>$$ \\\\left(g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right) . $$</p>\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-5-kg-is-moving-on-an-inclined-plane-which-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-uhh9mtwk6d9zovpl\"},{\"i\":34,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A particle of mass $m$ falls from rest through a resistive medium having resistive force, $F=-k v$, where $v$ is the velocity of the particle and $k$ is a constant. Which of the following graphs represents velocity $(v)$ versus time $(t)$ ?\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">7</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A particle of mass $m$ falls from rest through a resistive medium having resistive force, $F=-k v$, where $v$ is the velocity of the particle and $k$ is a constant. Which of the following graphs represents velocity $(v)$ versus time $(t)$ ?</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-particle-of-mass-m-falls-from-rest-through-a-resistiv-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-fcj0bfitbme6lnon\"},{\"i\":35,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A flexible chain of mass $m$ hangs between two fixed points at the same level. The inclination of the chain with the horizontal at the two points of support is $30^{\\\\circ}$. Considering the equilibrium of each half of the chain, the tension of the chain at the lowest point is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ .\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">8</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A flexible chain of mass $m$ hangs between two fixed points at the same level. The inclination of the chain with the horizontal at the two points of support is $30^{\\\\circ}$. Considering the equilibrium of each half of the chain, the tension of the chain at the lowest point is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ .</p>\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 24th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-flexible-chain-of-mass-m-hangs-between-two-fixed-poin-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-fxd5mwzwso8lb7v5\"},{\"i\":36,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block is sliding down on an inclined plane of slope $\\\\theta$ and at an instant $t=0$ this block is given an upward momentum so that it starts moving up on the inclined surface with velocity $u$. The distance $(S)$ travelled by the block before its velocity become zero, is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ . (g = gravitational acceleration)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">9</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block is sliding down on an inclined plane of slope $\\\\theta$ and at an instant $t=0$ this block is given an upward momentum so that it starts moving up on the inclined surface with velocity $u$. The distance $(S)$ travelled by the block before its velocity become zero, is $\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_\\\\_$ .</p>\\n<p>(g = gravitational acceleration)</p>\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 23rd January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-is-sliding-down-on-an-inclined-plane-of-slope-t-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-hmxaod6ircvnowaf\"},{\"i\":37,\"year\":2026,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A 4 kg mass moves under the influence of a force $\\\\vec{F}=\\\\left(4 t^3 \\\\hat{i}-3 t \\\\hat{j}\\\\right) \\\\mathrm{N}$ where $t$ is the time in second. If mass starts from origin at $t=0$, the velocity and position after $t=2 \\\\mathrm{~s}$ will be:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">10</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A 4 kg mass moves under the influence of a force $\\\\vec{F}=\\\\left(4 t^3 \\\\hat{i}-3 t \\\\hat{j}\\\\right) \\\\mathrm{N}$ where $t$ is the time in second. If mass starts from origin at $t=0$, the velocity and position after $t=2 \\\\mathrm{~s}$ will be:</p>\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2026 (Online) 21st January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-4-kg-mass-moves-under-the-influence-of-a-force-vecf-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-6drbp7jaz1aqske1\"},{\"i\":38,\"year\":2025,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass 2 kg moving with velocity of $ \\\\vec{v}_{in} = 3 \\\\hat{i} + 4 \\\\hat{j} \\\\text{ ms}^{-1} $ enters into a constant force field of 6N directed along positive z-axis. If the body remains in the field for a period of $ \\\\frac{5}{3} $ seconds, then velocity of th