ic friction between the box and horizontal surface is 0.3 then force of kinetic friction is :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-heavy-box-of-mass-50-mathrmkg-is-moving-on-a-ho-jee-main-physics-motion-q5mofxawtmifyopu\"},{\"i\":55,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A wooden block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ rests on a soft horizontal floor. When an iron cylinder of mass $$25 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed on the top of the block, the floor yields and the block and the cylinder together go down with an acceleration of $$0.1 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$. The action force of the system on the floor is equal to :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">28</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A wooden block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ rests on a soft horizontal floor. When an iron cylinder of mass $$25 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed on the top of the block, the floor yields and the block and the cylinder together go down with an acceleration of $$0.1 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$. The action force of the system on the floor is equal to :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-wooden-block-of-mass-5-mathrmkg-rests-on-a-soft-jee-main-physics-motion-2bqf6qdg8orlg4ev\"},{\"i\":56,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A $$2 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ brick begins to slide over a surface which is inclined at an angle of $$45^{\\\\circ}$$ with respect to horizontal axis. The co-efficient of static friction between their surfaces is:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">29</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A $$2 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ brick begins to slide over a surface which is inclined at an angle of $$45^{\\\\circ}$$ with respect to horizontal axis. The co-efficient of static friction between their surfaces is:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 4th April Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-2-mathrmkg-brick-begins-to-slide-over-a-surface-jee-main-physics-motion-pek94qv6fh8xtu5v\"},{\"i\":57,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A wooden block, initially at rest on the ground, is pushed by a force which increases linearly with time $$t$$. Which of the following curve best describes acceleration of the block with time :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">30</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A wooden block, initially at rest on the ground, is pushed by a force which increases linearly with time $$t$$. Which of the following curve best describes acceleration of the block with time :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 4th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-wooden-block-initially-at-rest-on-the-ground-is-pushe-jee-main-physics-motion-hi0e3qbtu63uxd5a\"},{\"i\":58,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass $4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ experiences two forces $\\\\vec{F}_1=5 \\\\hat{i}+8 \\\\hat{j}+7 \\\\hat{k}$ and $\\\\overrightarrow{\\\\mathrm{F}}_2=3 \\\\hat{i}-4 \\\\hat{j}-3 \\\\hat{k}$. The acceleration acting on the body is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">31</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A body of mass $4 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ experiences two forces $\\\\vec{F}_1=5 \\\\hat{i}+8 \\\\hat{j}+7 \\\\hat{k}$ and $\\\\overrightarrow{\\\\mathrm{F}}_2=3 \\\\hat{i}-4 \\\\hat{j}-3 \\\\hat{k}$. The acceleration acting on the body is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-body-of-mass-4-mathrmkg-experiences-two-forces-vec-jee-main-physics-imjgfe9evsqce6t7\"},{\"i\":59,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A cricket player catches a ball of mass $120 \\\\mathrm{~g}$ moving with $25 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$ speed. If the catching process is completed in $0.1 \\\\mathrm{~s}$ then the magnitude of force exerted by the ball on the hand of player will be (in SI unit) :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">32</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A cricket player catches a ball of mass $120 \\\\mathrm{~g}$ moving with $25 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$ speed. If the catching process is completed in $0.1 \\\\mathrm{~s}$ then the magnitude of force exerted by the ball on the hand of player will be (in SI unit) :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-cricket-player-catches-a-ball-of-mass-120-mathrmg-mo-jee-main-physics-8zuyl4bwvwakptlr\"},{\"i\":60,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Consider a block and trolley system as shown in figure. If the coefficient of kinetic friction between the trolley and the surface is 0.04 , the acceleration of the system in $\\\\mathrm{ms}^{-2}$ is : (Consider that the string is massless and unstretchable and the pulley is also massless and frictionless) :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">33</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Consider a block and trolley system as shown in figure. If the coefficient of kinetic friction between the trolley and the surface is 0.04 , the acceleration of the system in $\\\\mathrm{ms}^{-2}$ is :<br><br>\\n(Consider that the string is massless and unstretchable and the pulley is also massless and frictionless) :<br><br>\\n<img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsbnjxzt/77cd3c01-cb11-4d31-8c55-5ecc67830023/6850ac90-c5a4-11ee-9a31-4ff8d3b54e89/file-6y3zli1lsbnjxzu.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lsbnjxzt/77cd3c01-cb11-4d31-8c55-5ecc67830023/6850ac90-c5a4-11ee-9a31-4ff8d3b54e89/file-6y3zli1lsbnjxzu.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 1st February Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 42 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 1st February Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsbnjxzt/77cd3c01-cb11-4d31-8c55-5ecc67830023/6850ac90-c5a4-11ee-9a31-4ff8d3b54e89/file-6y3zli1lsbnjxzu.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/consider-a-block-and-trolley-system-as-shown-in-figure-if-t-jee-main-physics-4nzb3ntgjrshxm9a\"},{\"i\":61,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed on a rough inclined surface as shown in the figure. If $$\\\\overrightarrow{F_1}$$ is the force required to just move the block up the inclined plane and $$\\\\overrightarrow{F_2}$$ is the force required to just prevent the block from sliding down, then the value of $$\\\\left|\\\\overrightarrow{F_1}\\\\right|-\\\\left|\\\\overrightarrow{F_2}\\\\right|$$ is : [Use $$\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right]$$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">34</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsdw3lxp/c0d83cb9-329a-40f5-8aae-a8eed4326b04/6583b0c0-c6df-11ee-922e-e5cc8adab620/file-6y3zli1lsdw3lxq.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lsdw3lxp/c0d83cb9-329a-40f5-8aae-a8eed4326b04/6583b0c0-c6df-11ee-922e-e5cc8adab620/file-6y3zli1lsdw3lxq.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 39 English\\\"></p>\\n<p>A block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed on a rough inclined surface as shown in the figure. If $$\\\\overrightarrow{F_1}$$ is the force required to just move the block up the inclined plane and $$\\\\overrightarrow{F_2}$$ is the force required to just prevent the block from sliding down, then the value of $$\\\\left|\\\\overrightarrow{F_1}\\\\right|-\\\\left|\\\\overrightarrow{F_2}\\\\right|$$ is : [Use $$\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2\\\\right]$$</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsdw3lxp/c0d83cb9-329a-40f5-8aae-a8eed4326b04/6583b0c0-c6df-11ee-922e-e5cc8adab620/file-6y3zli1lsdw3lxq.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pimagep-pa-block-of-mass-5-mathrmkg-is-placed-jee-main-physics-motion-lcxxz9d1cdlmednn\"},{\"i\":62,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A light string passing over a smooth light fixed pulley connects two blocks of masses $$m_1$$ and $$m_2$$. If the acceleration of the system is $$g / 8$$, then the ratio of masses is:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">35</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A light string passing over a smooth light fixed pulley connects two blocks of masses $$m_1$$ and $$m_2$$. If the acceleration of the system is $$g / 8$$, then the ratio of masses is:</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsdw5gzh/c538fef0-b8dd-45cc-9f8f-7fd5f215b971/994f1ed0-c6df-11ee-878f-6db133fe392f/file-6y3zli1lsdw5gzi.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lsdw5gzh/c538fef0-b8dd-45cc-9f8f-7fd5f215b971/994f1ed0-c6df-11ee-878f-6db133fe392f/file-6y3zli1lsdw5gzi.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 40 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsdw5gzh/c538fef0-b8dd-45cc-9f8f-7fd5f215b971/994f1ed0-c6df-11ee-878f-6db133fe392f/file-6y3zli1lsdw5gzi.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-light-string-passing-over-a-smooth-light-fixed-pulley-c-jee-main-physics-motion-4nbhsaa3nw7qclur\"},{\"i\":63,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"In the given arrangement of a doubly inclined plane two blocks of masses $$M$$ and $$m$$ are placed. The blocks are connected by a light string passing over an ideal pulley as shown. The coefficient of friction between the surface of the plane and the blocks is 0.25. The value of $$m$$, for which $$M=10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ will move down with an acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$, is: (take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$ and $$\\\\left.\\\\tan 37^{\\\\circ}=3 / 4\\\\right)$$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">36</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>In the given arrangement of a doubly inclined plane two blocks of masses $$M$$ and $$m$$ are placed. The blocks are connected by a light string passing over an ideal pulley as shown. The coefficient of friction between the surface of the plane and the blocks is 0.25. The value of $$m$$, for which $$M=10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ will move down with an acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$, is: (take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^2$$ and $$\\\\left.\\\\tan 37^{\\\\circ}=3 / 4\\\\right)$$</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsegetv9/4e7f812c-55e9-4490-a023-e811c35d14e0/d4203e50-c72e-11ee-8cb5-7deab4010c9e/file-6y3zli1lsegetva.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lsegetv9/4e7f812c-55e9-4490-a023-e811c35d14e0/d4203e50-c72e-11ee-8cb5-7deab4010c9e/file-6y3zli1lsegetva.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 38 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lsegetv9/4e7f812c-55e9-4490-a023-e811c35d14e0/d4203e50-c72e-11ee-8cb5-7deab4010c9e/file-6y3zli1lsegetva.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pin-the-given-arrangement-of-a-doubly-inclined-plane-two-b-jee-main-physics-motion-uhamegxggt7jqgvh\"},{\"i\":64,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $$m$$ is placed on a surface having vertical crossection given by $$y=x^2 / 4$$. If coefficient of friction is 0.5, the maximum height above the ground at which block can be placed without slipping is:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">37</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass $$m$$ is placed on a surface having vertical crossection given by $$y=x^2 / 4$$. If coefficient of friction is 0.5, the maximum height above the ground at which block can be placed without slipping is:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-m-is-placed-on-a-surface-having-verti-jee-main-physics-motion-upggcykbejlgodbx\"},{\"i\":65,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Three blocks $$A, B$$ and $$C$$ are pulled on a horizontal smooth surface by a force of $$80 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ as shown in figure The tensions T$$_1$$ and T$$_2$$ in the string are respectively :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">38</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Three blocks $$A, B$$ and $$C$$ are pulled on a horizontal smooth surface by a force of $$80 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ as shown in figure</p>\\n\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lshjch7s/7590b147-1224-42e5-bef6-4bd85914789c/a811ea80-c8e0-11ee-8501-bb04786aa212/file-6y3zli1lshjch7t.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lshjch7s/7590b147-1224-42e5-bef6-4bd85914789c/a811ea80-c8e0-11ee-8501-bb04786aa212/file-6y3zli1lshjch7t.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 37 English\\\"></p>\\n\\n<p>The tensions T$$_1$$ and T$$_2$$ in the string are respectively :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lshjch7s/7590b147-1224-42e5-bef6-4bd85914789c/a811ea80-c8e0-11ee-8501-bb04786aa212/file-6y3zli1lshjch7t.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthree-blocks-a-b-and-c-are-pulled-on-a-horizonta-jee-main-physics-motion-wrrklxsv17h2shap\"},{\"i\":66,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"All surfaces shown in figure are assumed to be frictionless and the pulleys and the string are light. The acceleration of the block of mass $$2 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">39</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>All surfaces shown in figure are assumed to be frictionless and the pulleys and the string are light. The acceleration of the block of mass $$2 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is :</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lshfe4i3/5c7622f4-9684-4975-b99d-6b1f7816a284/3159c1b0-c8d1-11ee-adc8-974b9031006b/file-6y3zli1lshfe4i4.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lshfe4i3/5c7622f4-9684-4975-b99d-6b1f7816a284/3159c1b0-c8d1-11ee-adc8-974b9031006b/file-6y3zli1lshfe4i4.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 30th January Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 35 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 30th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lshfe4i3/5c7622f4-9684-4975-b99d-6b1f7816a284/3159c1b0-c8d1-11ee-adc8-974b9031006b/file-6y3zli1lshfe4i4.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pall-surfaces-shown-in-figure-are-assumed-to-be-frictionle-jee-main-physics-motion-x2hz0ijoxpwayjyi\"},{\"i\":67,\"year\":2024,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Given below are two statements : Statement (I) : The limiting force of static friction depends on the area of contact and independent of materials. Statement (II) : The limiting force of kinetic friction is independent of the area of contact and depends on materials. In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">40</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Given below are two statements :</p>\\n<p>Statement (I) : The limiting force of static friction depends on the area of contact and independent of materials.</p>\\n<p>Statement (II) : The limiting force of kinetic friction is independent of the area of contact and depends on materials.</p>\\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2024 (Online) 27th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pgiven-below-are-two-statements-p-pstatement-i--t-jee-main-physics-motion-ripwpekdogx8b59z\"},{\"i\":68,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"The position vector of a particle related to time $t$ is given by $\\\\vec{r}=\\\\left(10 t \\\\hat{i}+15 t^{2} \\\\hat{j}+7 \\\\hat{k}\\\\right) m$ The direction of net force experienced by the particle is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">41</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">The position vector of a particle related to time $t$ is given by\\n<br><br>\\n$\\\\vec{r}=\\\\left(10 t \\\\hat{i}+15 t^{2} \\\\hat{j}+7 \\\\hat{k}\\\\right) m$\\n<br><br>\\nThe direction of net force experienced by the particle is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 15th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/the-position-vector-of-a-particle-related-to-time-t-is-giv-jee-main-physics-f92bhchcr6xkucdp\"},{\"i\":69,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Three forces $$F_{1}=10 \\\\mathrm{~N}, F_{2}=8 \\\\mathrm{~N}, \\\\mathrm{~F}_{3}=6 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ are acting on a particle of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$. The forces $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{2}$$ and $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{3}$$ are applied perpendicularly so that particle remains at rest. If the force $$F_{1}$$ is removed, then the acceleration of the particle is:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">42</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Three forces $$F_{1}=10 \\\\mathrm{~N}, F_{2}=8 \\\\mathrm{~N}, \\\\mathrm{~F}_{3}=6 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ are acting on a particle of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$. The forces $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{2}$$ and $$\\\\mathrm{F}_{3}$$ are applied perpendicularly so that particle remains at rest. If the force $$F_{1}$$ is removed, then the acceleration of the particle is:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 12th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthree-forces-f110-mathrmn-f28-mathrmn-jee-main-physics-motion-9yoh2gp54k1jcza6\"},{\"i\":70,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A body of mass $$500 \\\\mathrm{~g}$$ moves along $$\\\\mathrm{x}$$-axis such that it's velocity varies with displacement $$\\\\mathrm{x}$$ according to the relation $$v=10 \\\\sqrt{x} \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$$ the force acting on the body is:-\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">43</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A body of mass $$500 \\\\mathrm{~g}$$ moves along $$\\\\mathrm{x}$$-axis such that it's velocity varies with displacement $$\\\\mathrm{x}$$ according to the relation $$v=10 \\\\sqrt{x} \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$$ the force acting on the body is:-</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 11th April Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-body-of-mass-500-mathrmg-moves-along-mathrm-jee-main-physics-motion-xfjjhoxvlxtkp8rq\"},{\"i\":71,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"At any instant the velocity of a particle of mass $$500 \\\\mathrm{~g}$$ is $$\\\\left(2 t \\\\hat{i}+3 t^{2} \\\\hat{j}\\\\right) \\\\mathrm{ms}^{-1}$$. If the force acting on the particle at $$t=1 \\\\mathrm{~s}$$ is $$(\\\\hat{i}+x \\\\hat{j}) \\\\mathrm{N}$$. Then the value of $$x$$ will be:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">44</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>At any instant the velocity of a particle of mass $$500 \\\\mathrm{~g}$$ is $$\\\\left(2 t \\\\hat{i}+3 t^{2} \\\\hat{j}\\\\right) \\\\mathrm{ms}^{-1}$$. If the force acting on the particle at $$t=1 \\\\mathrm{~s}$$ is $$(\\\\hat{i}+x \\\\hat{j}) \\\\mathrm{N}$$. Then the value of $$x$$ will be:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 8th April Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pat-any-instant-the-velocity-of-a-particle-of-mass-500--jee-main-physics-motion-3dbiorgpyageeo7r\"},{\"i\":72,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"As shown in the figure a block of mass 10 kg lying on a horizontal surface is pulled by a force F acting at an angle $$30^\\\\circ$$, with horizontal. For $$\\\\mu_s=0.25$$, the block will just start to move for the value of F : [Given $$g=10~\\\\mathrm{ms}^{-2}$$]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">45</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>As shown in the figure a block of mass 10 kg lying on a horizontal surface is pulled by a force F acting at an angle $$30^\\\\circ$$, with horizontal. For $$\\\\mu_s=0.25$$, the block will just start to move for the value of F : [Given $$g=10~\\\\mathrm{ms}^{-2}$$]</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldod97rg/b5c4601b-ab20-46db-9d22-b759ede73d09/146d5cc0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldod97rh.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldod97rg/b5c4601b-ab20-46db-9d22-b759ede73d09/146d5cc0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldod97rh.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 60 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldod97rg/b5c4601b-ab20-46db-9d22-b759ede73d09/146d5cc0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldod97rh.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pas-shown-in-the-figure-a-block-of-mass-10-kg-lying-on-a-h-jee-main-physics-motion-kbfxxken9bbhnygh\"},{\"i\":73,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Figures (a), (b), (c) and (d) show variation of force with time. The impulse is highest in figure.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">46</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Figures (a), (b), (c) and (d) show variation of force with time.</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldodevx5/697d42ac-e581-4144-a577-2c890a64d1d1/b22297a0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldodevx6.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldodevx5/697d42ac-e581-4144-a577-2c890a64d1d1/b22297a0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldodevx6.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 65vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 59 English\\\"></p>\\n<p>The impulse is highest in figure.</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 1st February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldodevx5/697d42ac-e581-4144-a577-2c890a64d1d1/b22297a0-a3ab-11ed-bed3-417993225459/file-1ldodevx6.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pfigures-a-b-c-and-d-show-variation-of-force-wit-jee-main-physics-motion-6irlhj20kaudrgds\"},{\"i\":74,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed at rest on a table of rough surface. Now, if a force of $$30 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ is applied in the direction parallel to surface of the table, the block slides through a distance of $$50 \\\\mathrm{~m}$$ in an interval of time $$10 \\\\mathrm{~s}$$. Coefficient of kinetic friction is (given, $$g=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$):\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">47</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass $$5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed at rest on a table of rough surface. Now, if a force of $$30 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ is applied in the direction parallel to surface of the table, the block slides through a distance of $$50 \\\\mathrm{~m}$$ in an interval of time $$10 \\\\mathrm{~s}$$. Coefficient of kinetic friction is (given, $$g=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$):</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 202