lass=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>As shown in figure, a $$70 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ garden roller is pushed with a force of $$\\\\vec{F}=200 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$ at an angle of $$30^{\\\\circ}$$ with horizontal. The normal reaction on the roller is</p>\\n<p>(Given $$\\\\mathrm{g=10~m~s^{-2}}$$)</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldq05cb3/91a81a0a-30e8-4e92-b28b-291e638a7f71/635261f0-a491-11ed-8eb4-ef270ed2fedb/file-1ldq05cb4.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldq05cb3/91a81a0a-30e8-4e92-b28b-291e638a7f71/635261f0-a491-11ed-8eb4-ef270ed2fedb/file-1ldq05cb4.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 31st January Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 56 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 31st January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldq05cb3/91a81a0a-30e8-4e92-b28b-291e638a7f71/635261f0-a491-11ed-8eb4-ef270ed2fedb/file-1ldq05cb4.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pas-shown-in-figure-a-70-mathrmkg-garden-roller-i-jee-main-physics-motion-j7jlcabiyeak0dhq\"},{\"i\":77,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of $\\\\sqrt{3} \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ is attached to a string whose other end is attached to the wall. An unknown force $\\\\mathrm{F}$ is applied so that the string makes an angle of $30^{\\\\circ}$ with the wall. The tension $\\\\mathrm{T}$ is: (Given $\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$ )\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">50</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of $\\\\sqrt{3} \\\\mathrm{~kg}$ is attached to a string whose other end is attached to the wall. An unknown force $\\\\mathrm{F}$ is applied so that the string makes an angle of $30^{\\\\circ}$ with the wall. The tension $\\\\mathrm{T}$ is:\\n(Given $\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$ )<br><br>\\n<img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldqydxm8/9459b9ba-83cf-4b5e-b0bc-46470dfbd13c/48a5a700-a517-11ed-868c-9b3df14ba4de/file-1ldqydxm9.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldqydxm8/9459b9ba-83cf-4b5e-b0bc-46470dfbd13c/48a5a700-a517-11ed-868c-9b3df14ba4de/file-1ldqydxm9.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 55 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldqydxm8/9459b9ba-83cf-4b5e-b0bc-46470dfbd13c/48a5a700-a517-11ed-868c-9b3df14ba4de/file-1ldqydxm9.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-sqrt3-mathrmkg-is-attached-to-a-string-w-jee-main-physics-8o0ckwokotsevvjj\"},{\"i\":78,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A force acts for 20 s on a body of mass 20 kg, starting from rest, after which the force ceases and then body describes 50 m in the next 10 s. The value of force will be:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">51</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A force acts for 20 s on a body of mass 20 kg, starting from rest, after which the force ceases and then body describes 50 m in the next 10 s. The value of force will be:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-force-acts-for-20-s-on-a-body-of-mass-20-kg-starting-f-jee-main-physics-motion-hsut1g7rwijltj3p\"},{\"i\":79,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"The time taken by an object to slide down 45$$^\\\\circ$$ rough inclined plane is n times as it takes to slide down a perfectly smooth 45$$^\\\\circ$$ incline plane. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the object and the incline plane is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">52</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>The time taken by an object to slide down 45$$^\\\\circ$$ rough inclined plane is n times as it takes to slide down a perfectly smooth 45$$^\\\\circ$$ incline plane. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the object and the incline plane is :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthe-time-taken-by-an-object-to-slide-down-45circ-ro-jee-main-physics-motion-bshx1j1fsuday1hr\"},{\"i\":80,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $m$ slides down the plane inclined at angle $$30^{\\\\circ}$$ with an acceleration $$\\\\frac{g}{4}$$. The value of coefficient of kinetic friction will be:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">53</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass $m$ slides down the plane inclined at angle $$30^{\\\\circ}$$ with an acceleration $$\\\\frac{g}{4}$$. The value of coefficient of kinetic friction will be:</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 29th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-m-slides-down-the-plane-inclined-at-ang-jee-main-physics-motion-ndvhprxthiulgtuq\"},{\"i\":81,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Consider a block kept on an inclined plane (incline at 45$$^\\\\circ$$) as shown in the figure. If the force required to just push it up the incline is 2 times the force required to just prevent it from sliding down, the coefficient of friction between the block and inclined plane($$\\\\mu$$) is equal to :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">54</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Consider a block kept on an inclined plane (incline at 45$$^\\\\circ$$) as shown in the figure. If the force required to just push it up the incline is 2 times the force required to just prevent it from sliding down, the coefficient of friction between the block and inclined plane($$\\\\mu$$) is equal to :</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldufajnc/e3a484ec-cc82-4fe8-a831-03555b0e60b4/bf927070-a6ff-11ed-8109-3974114a046e/file-1ldufajnd.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldufajnc/e3a484ec-cc82-4fe8-a831-03555b0e60b4/bf927070-a6ff-11ed-8109-3974114a046e/file-1ldufajnd.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 25th January Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 51 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 25th January Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldufajnc/e3a484ec-cc82-4fe8-a831-03555b0e60b4/bf927070-a6ff-11ed-8109-3974114a046e/file-1ldufajnd.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pconsider-a-block-kept-on-an-inclined-plane-incline-at-45-jee-main-physics-motion-3qmjuvepa8ymjlc3\"},{\"i\":82,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"As per given figure, a weightless pulley P is attached on a double inclined frictionless surfaces. The tension in the string (massless) will be (if g = 10 m/s$$^2$$)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">55</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>As per given figure, a weightless pulley P is attached on a double inclined frictionless surfaces. The tension in the string (massless) will be (if g = 10 m/s$$^2$$)</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldzib2k8/4f80eb0c-2b56-4d65-8235-9110df0e5bc0/74d11c70-a9cb-11ed-8808-21af647bf8f1/file-1ldzib2k9.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldzib2k8/4f80eb0c-2b56-4d65-8235-9110df0e5bc0/74d11c70-a9cb-11ed-8808-21af647bf8f1/file-1ldzib2k9.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 24th January Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 50 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 24th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldzib2k8/4f80eb0c-2b56-4d65-8235-9110df0e5bc0/74d11c70-a9cb-11ed-8808-21af647bf8f1/file-1ldzib2k9.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pas-per-given-figure-a-weightless-pulley-p-is-attached-on-jee-main-physics-motion-5p3mcjwz0i2sxkwt\"},{\"i\":83,\"year\":2023,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Given below are two statements : Statement I : An elevator can go up or down with uniform speed when its weight is balanced with the tension of its cable. Statement II : Force exerted by the floor of an elevator on the foot of a person standing on it is more than his/her weight when the elevator goes down with increasing speed. In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">56</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Given below are two statements :</p>\\n<p>Statement I : An elevator can go up or down with uniform speed when its weight is balanced with the tension of its cable.</p>\\n<p>Statement II : Force exerted by the floor of an elevator on the foot of a person standing on it  is more than his/her weight when the elevator goes down with increasing speed.</p>\\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2023 (Online) 24th January Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pgiven-below-are-two-statements-p-pstatement-i--an-jee-main-physics-motion-fvfrsqavpiehgg62\"},{\"i\":84,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Two bodies of masses $$m_{1}=5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$m_{2}=3 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ are connected by a light string going over a smooth light pulley on a smooth inclined plane as shown in the figure. The system is at rest. The force exerted by the inclined plane on the body of mass $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{1}$$ will be : [Take $$\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}\\\\right]$$\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">57</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Two bodies of masses $$m_{1}=5 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$m_{2}=3 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ are connected by a light string going over a smooth light pulley on a smooth inclined plane as shown in the figure. The system is at rest. The force exerted by the inclined plane on the body of mass $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{1}$$ will be : [Take $$\\\\left.\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}\\\\right]$$</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6tbf6ez/4e8f3268-f9d9-4ffb-8f40-d2700d9606f0/4f9410b0-1bce-11ed-bd9f-71db3a4811b2/file-1l6tbf6f0.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6tbf6ez/4e8f3268-f9d9-4ffb-8f40-d2700d9606f0/4f9410b0-1bce-11ed-bd9f-71db3a4811b2/file-1l6tbf6f0.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 29th July Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 61 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 29th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6tbf6ez/4e8f3268-f9d9-4ffb-8f40-d2700d9606f0/4f9410b0-1bce-11ed-bd9f-71db3a4811b2/file-1l6tbf6f0.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/ptwo-bodies-of-masses-m15-mathrmkg-and-m2-jee-main-physics-motion-vp0u4d0u5dgx21ph\"},{\"i\":85,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A uniform metal chain of mass m and length 'L' passes over a massless and frictionless pulley. It is released from rest with a part of its length 'l' is hanging on one side and rest of its length '$$\\\\mathrm{L}-l$$' is hanging on the other side of the pully. At a certain point of time, when $$l=\\\\frac{L}{x}$$, the acceleration of the chain is $$\\\\frac{g}{2}$$. The value of x is __________.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">58</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A uniform metal chain of mass m and length 'L' passes over a massless and frictionless pulley. It is released from rest with a part of its length 'l' is hanging on one side and rest of its length '$$\\\\mathrm{L}-l$$' is hanging on the other side of the pully. At a certain point of time, when $$l=\\\\frac{L}{x}$$, the acceleration of the chain is $$\\\\frac{g}{2}$$. The value of x is __________.</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6s8dia7/90ac58ae-aab0-4f5d-b0c5-d97efb1a2b07/9d1725f0-1b35-11ed-9b6a-df095ce8d5ea/file-1l6s8dia8.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6s8dia7/90ac58ae-aab0-4f5d-b0c5-d97efb1a2b07/9d1725f0-1b35-11ed-9b6a-df095ce8d5ea/file-1l6s8dia8.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 28th July Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 62 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 28th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6s8dia7/90ac58ae-aab0-4f5d-b0c5-d97efb1a2b07/9d1725f0-1b35-11ed-9b6a-df095ce8d5ea/file-1l6s8dia8.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-uniform-metal-chain-of-mass-m-and-length-l-passes-ove-jee-main-physics-motion-rugsltezkoyk66yv\"},{\"i\":86,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass M slides down on a rough inclined plane with constant velocity. The angle made by the incline plane with horizontal is $$\\\\theta$$. The magnitude of the contact force will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">59</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass M slides down on a rough inclined plane with constant velocity. The angle made by the incline plane with horizontal is $$\\\\theta$$. The magnitude of the contact force will be :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-m-slides-down-on-a-rough-inclined-plane-w-jee-main-physics-motion-hpwd22umsjvstb1j\"},{\"i\":87,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block 'A' takes 2 s to slide down a frictionless incline of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ and length 'l', kept inside a lift going up with uniform velocity 'v'. If the incline is changed to 45$$^\\\\circ$$, the time taken by the block, to slide down the incline, will be approximately :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">60</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block 'A' takes 2 s to slide down a frictionless incline of 30$$^\\\\circ$$ and length 'l', kept inside a lift going up with uniform velocity 'v'. If the incline is changed to 45$$^\\\\circ$$, the time taken by the block, to slide down the incline, will be approximately :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-a-takes-2-s-to-slide-down-a-frictionless-inclin-jee-main-physics-motion-arm0rndbml5ldivc\"},{\"i\":88,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A bag is gently dropped on a conveyor belt moving at a speed of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$$. The coefficient of friction between the conveyor belt and bag is $$0.4$$. Initially, the bag slips on the belt before it stops due to friction. The distance travelled by the bag on the belt during slipping motion, is : [Take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{-2}$$ ]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">61</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A bag is gently dropped on a conveyor belt moving at a speed of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}$$. The coefficient of friction between the conveyor belt and bag is $$0.4$$. Initially, the bag slips on the belt before it stops due to friction. The distance travelled by the bag on the belt during slipping motion, is : [Take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{-2}$$ ]</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th July Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-bag-is-gently-dropped-on-a-conveyor-belt-moving-at-a-sp-jee-main-physics-motion-eq1jkao0fu8h6s8v\"},{\"i\":89,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Two masses $$M_{1}$$ and $$M_{2}$$ are tied together at the two ends of a light inextensible string that passes over a frictionless pulley. When the mass $$M_{2}$$ is twice that of $$M_{1}$$, the acceleration of the system is $$a_{1}$$. When the mass $$M_{2}$$ is thrice that of $$M_{1}$$, the acceleration of the system is $$a_{2}$$. The ratio $$\\\\frac{a_{1}}{a_{2}}$$ will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">62</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Two masses $$M_{1}$$ and $$M_{2}$$ are tied together at the two ends of a light inextensible string that passes over a frictionless pulley. When the mass $$M_{2}$$ is twice that of $$M_{1}$$, the acceleration of the system is $$a_{1}$$. When the mass $$M_{2}$$ is thrice that of $$M_{1}$$, the acceleration of the system is $$a_{2}$$. The ratio $$\\\\frac{a_{1}}{a_{2}}$$ will be :</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6kpbi3o/c611f556-d8e9-44a5-8fce-c8aa07f62e83/9b551240-1711-11ed-8e2a-2927a6806d88/file-1l6kpbi3p.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6kpbi3o/c611f556-d8e9-44a5-8fce-c8aa07f62e83/9b551240-1711-11ed-8e2a-2927a6806d88/file-1l6kpbi3p.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th July Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 67 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6kpbi3o/c611f556-d8e9-44a5-8fce-c8aa07f62e83/9b551240-1711-11ed-8e2a-2927a6806d88/file-1l6kpbi3p.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/ptwo-masses-m1-and-m2-are-tied-together-at-t-jee-main-physics-motion-epzbgb4mfmdyubhq\"},{\"i\":90,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"Three masses $$M=100 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, \\\\mathrm{~m}_{1}=10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{2}=20 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ are arranged in a system as shown in figure. All the surfaces are frictionless and strings are inextensible and weightless. The pulleys are also weightless and frictionless. A force $$\\\\mathrm{F}$$ is applied on the system so that the mass $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{2}$$ moves upward with an acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$. The value of $$\\\\mathrm{F}$$ is : ( Take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$ )\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">63</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>Three masses $$M=100 \\\\mathrm{~kg}, \\\\mathrm{~m}_{1}=10 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ and $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{2}=20 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ are arranged in a system as shown in figure. All the surfaces are frictionless and strings are inextensible and weightless. The pulleys are also weightless and frictionless. A force $$\\\\mathrm{F}$$ is applied on the system so that the mass $$\\\\mathrm{m}_{2}$$ moves upward with an acceleration of $$2 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$. The value of $$\\\\mathrm{F}$$ is :</p>\\n<p>( Take $$\\\\mathrm{g}=10 \\\\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$$ )</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6hyfacn/cbd8544e-bc0a-4629-b797-623cfa071856/dccbb370-158e-11ed-8619-9f3c88c71b51/file-1l6hyfaco.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6hyfacn/cbd8544e-bc0a-4629-b797-623cfa071856/dccbb370-158e-11ed-8619-9f3c88c71b51/file-1l6hyfaco.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th July Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 69 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th July Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6hyfacn/cbd8544e-bc0a-4629-b797-623cfa071856/dccbb370-158e-11ed-8619-9f3c88c71b51/file-1l6hyfaco.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pthree-masses-m100-mathrmkg-mathrmm110-ma-jee-main-physics-motion-608huhcahmavfl0v\"},{\"i\":91,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A monkey of mass $$50 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ climbs on a rope which can withstand the tension (T) of $$350 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$. If monkey initially climbs down with an acceleration of $$4 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$ and then climbs up with an acceleration of $$5 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$. Choose the correct option $$\\\\left(g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}\\\\right)$$.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">64</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A monkey of mass $$50 \\\\mathrm{~kg}$$ climbs on a rope which can withstand the tension (T) of $$350 \\\\mathrm{~N}$$. If monkey initially climbs down with an acceleration of $$4 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$ and then climbs up with an acceleration of $$5 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}$$. Choose the correct option $$\\\\left(g=10 \\\\mathrm{~m} / \\\\mathrm{s}^{2}\\\\right)$$.</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th July Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-monkey-of-mass-50-mathrmkg-climbs-on-a-rope-whi-jee-main-physics-motion-durhawel3zkbrjgg\"},{\"i\":92,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"For a free body diagram shown in the figure, the four forces are applied in the 'x' and 'y' directions. What additional force must be applied and at what angle with positive x-axis so that the net acceleration of body is zero?\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">65</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>For a free body diagram shown in the figure, the four forces are applied in the 'x' and 'y' directions. What additional force must be applied and at what angle with positive x-axis so that the net acceleration of body is zero?</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6gjqx2z/c4697746-f981-4180-99a6-0a851562c47c/aeab4cb0-14c8-11ed-9a57-873b3ac09d5c/file-1l6gjqx30.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l6gjqx2z/c4697746-f981-4180-99a6-0a851562c47c/aeab4cb0-14c8-11ed-9a57-873b3ac09d5c/file-1l6gjqx30.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 25th July Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 70 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 25th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l6gjqx2z/c4697746-f981-4180-99a6-0a851562c47c/aeab4cb0-14c8-11ed-9a57-873b3ac09d5c/file-1l6gjqx30.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pfor-a-free-body-diagram-shown-in-the-figure-the-four-for-jee-main-physics-motion-gvgstazkliyaxznj\"},{\"i\":93,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A 2 kg block is pushed against a vertical wall by applying a horizontal force of 50 N. The coefficient of static friction between the block and the wall is 0.5. A force F is also applied on the block vertically upward (as shown in figure). The maximum value of F applied, so that the block does not move upward, will be : (Given : g = 10 ms$$-$$2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">66</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A 2 kg block is pushed against a vertical wall by applying a horizontal force of 50 N. The coefficient of static friction between the block and the wall is 0.5. A force F is also applied on the block vertically upward (as shown in figure). The maximum value of F applied, so that the block does not move upward, will be :</p>\\n<p>(Given : g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>)</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5wighcu/bc7a3021-27b2-4d27-8610-c1aeb2bdbe40/f64fc8d0-09c3-11ed-aacd-cd06ee4162a1/file-1l5wighcv.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l5wighcu/bc7a3021-27b2-4d27-8610-c1aeb2bdbe40/f64fc8d0-09c3-11ed-aacd-cd06ee4162a1/file-1l5wighcv.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 30th June Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 72 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 30th June Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5wighcu/bc7a3021-27b2-4d27-8610-c1aeb2bdbe40/f64fc8d0-09c3-11ed-aacd-cd06ee4162a1/file-1l5wighcv.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-2-kg-block-is-pushed-against-a-vertical-wall-by-applyin-jee-main-physics-motion-sbebfulopymvbj5d\"},{\"i\":94,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 40 kg slides over a surface, when a mass of 4 kg is suspended through an inextensible massless string passing over frictionless pulley as shown below. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the surface and block is 0.02. The acceleration of block is. (Given g = 10 ms$$-$$2.)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">67</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass 40 kg slides over a surface, when a mass of 4 kg is suspended through an inextensible massless string passing over frictionless pulley as shown below.</p>\\n<p>The coefficient of kinetic friction between the surface and block is 0.02. The acceleration of block is. (Given g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>.)</p>\\n<p> <img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l55fktpc/4f8be818-5ada-45af-ac03-4cbb21cbe447/8a2a1ef0-fadf-11ec-830f-2bceee3af987/file-1l55fktpd.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l55fktpc/4f8be818-5ada-45af-ac03-4cbb21cbe447/8a2a1ef0-fadf-11ec-830f-2bceee3af987/file-1l55fktpd.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 29th June Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 85 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 29th June Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l55fktpc/4f8be818-5ada-45af-ac03-4cbb21cbe447/8a2a1ef0-fadf-11ec-830f-2bceee3af987/file-1l55fktpd.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-40-kg-slides-over-a-surface-when-a-mass-jee-main-physics-motion-smypwyxsjxmwh7zt\"},{\"i\":95,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass M placed inside a box descends vertically with acceleration 'a'. The block exerts a force equal to one-fourth of its weight on the floor of the box. The value of 'a' will be\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">68</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass M placed inside a box descends vertically with acceleration 'a'. The block exerts a force equal to one-fourth of its weight on the floor of the box. The value of 'a' will be</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 29th June Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-m-placed-inside-a-box-descends-vertically-jee-main-physics-motion-yyaqmjep9ojwxpws\"},{\"i\":96,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 2 kg moving on a horizontal surface with speed of 4 ms$$-$$1 enters a rough surface ranging from x = 0.5 m to x = 1.5 m. The retarding force in this range of rough surface is related to distance by F = $$-$$kx where k = 12 Nm$$-$$1. The speed of the block as it just crosses the rough surface will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">69</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass 2 kg moving on a horizontal surface with speed of 4 ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup> enters a rough surface ranging from x = 0.5 m to x = 1.5 m. The retarding force in this range of rough surface is related to distance by F = $$-$$kx where k = 12 Nm<sup>$$-$$1</sup>. The speed of the block as it just crosses the rough surface will be :</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 28th June Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-2-kg-moving-on-a-horizontal-surface-with-jee-main-physics-motion-96ggio0lapyoymsa\"},{\"i\":97,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A system of two blocks of masses m = 2 kg and M = 8 kg is placed on a smooth table as shown in figure. The coefficient of static friction between two blocks is 0.5. The maximum horizontal force F that can be applied to the block of mass M so that the blocks move together will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">70</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A system of two blocks of masses m = 2 kg and M = 8 kg is placed on a smooth table as shown in figure. The coefficient of static friction between two blocks is 0.5. The maximum horizontal force F that can be applied to the block of mass M so that the blocks move together will be :</p>\\n<p> <img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l58kskgh/07d7baeb-b299-4128-a2d7-963887729e01/49170010-fc9a-11ec-9d77-21bb74d9ea0a/file-1l58kskgi.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l58kskgh/07d7baeb-b299-4128-a2d7-963887729e01/49170010-fc9a-11ec-9d77-21bb74d9ea0a/file-1l58kskgi.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th June Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 80 English\\\"> </p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 27th June Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l58kskgh/07d7baeb-b299-4128-a2d7-963887729e01/49170010-fc9a-11ec-9d77-21bb74d9ea0a/file-1l58kskgi.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-system-of-two-blocks-of-masses-m--2-kg-and-m--8-kg-is-jee-main-physics-motion-i6ovp2fda8kducda\"},{\"i\":98,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"In the arrangement shown in figure a1, a2, a3 and a4 are the accelerations of masses m1, m2, m3 and m4 respectively. Which of the following relation is true for this arrangement?\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">71</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>In the arrangement shown in figure a<sub>1</sub>, a<sub>2</sub>, a<sub>3</sub> and a<sub>4</sub> are the accelerations of masses m<sub>1</sub>, m<sub>2</sub>, m<sub>3</sub> and m<sub>4</sub> respectively. Which of the following relation is true for this arrangement?</p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5ah1ydy/4960bf07-d070-4696-a462-2d0eddf45242/3aea2f60-fda5-11ec-9375-7dc6a3ea1387/file-1l5ah1ydz.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l5ah1ydy/4960bf07-d070-4696-a462-2d0eddf45242/3aea2f60-fda5-11ec-9375-7dc6a3ea1387/file-1l5ah1ydz.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th June Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 78 English\\\"></p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th June Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5ah1ydy/4960bf07-d070-4696-a462-2d0eddf45242/3aea2f60-fda5-11ec-9375-7dc6a3ea1387/file-1l5ah1ydz.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pin-the-arrangement-shown-in-figure-asub1sub-asub2-jee-main-physics-motion-ye9usg24nfz5kfmk\"},{\"i\":99,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A person is standing in an elevator. In which situation, he experiences weight loss?\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">72</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A person is standing in an elevator. In which situation, he experiences weight loss?</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 26th June Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-person-is-standing-in-an-elevator-in-which-situation-jee-main-physics-motion-eblcyvbvzehjd9sd\"},{\"i\":100,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"An object of mass 5 kg is thrown vertically upwards from the ground. The air resistance produces a constant retarding force of 10 N throughout the motion. The ratio of time of ascent to the time of descent will be equal to : [Use g = 10 ms$$-$$2].\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">73</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>An object of mass 5 kg is thrown vertically upwards from the ground. The air resistance produces a constant retarding force of 10 N throughout the motion. The ratio of time of ascent to the time of descent will be equal to : [Use g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>].</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 24th June Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pan-object-of-mass-5-kg-is-thrown-vertically-upwards-from-jee-main-physics-motion-samgpkhlseiitu3q\"},{\"i\":101,\"year\":2022,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 10 kg starts sliding on a surface with an initial velocity of 9.8 ms$$-$$1. The coefficient of friction between the surface and block is 0.5. The distance covered by the block before coming to rest is : [use g = 9.8 ms$$-$$2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">74</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><p>A block of mass 10 kg starts sliding on a surface with an initial velocity of 9.8 ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup>. The coefficient of friction between the surface and block is 0.5. The distance covered by the block before coming to rest is :</p>\\n<p>[use g = 9.8 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>]</p></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2022 (Online) 24th June Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/pa-block-of-mass-10-kg-starts-sliding-on-a-surface-with-an-jee-main-physics-motion-xvg5gnullifrecyd\"},{\"i\":102,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass m slides on the wooden wedge, which in turn slides backward on the horizontal surface. The acceleration of the block with respect to the wedge is : Given m = 8 kg, M = 16 kg Assume all the surfaces shown in the figure to be frictionless.\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">75</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass m slides on the wooden wedge, which in turn slides backward on the horizontal surface. The acceleration of the block with respect to the wedge is : Given m = 8 kg, M = 16 kg Assume all the surfaces shown in the figure to be frictionless.<br><br>\\n<img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kwlekg3k/dba4a1f6-c0be-4b58-b7b5-9b523266b4d4/2e81c800-517a-11ec-b1ae-c1b029d25cc4/file-1kwlekg3l.jpeg?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kwlekg3k/dba4a1f6-c0be-4b58-b7b5-9b523266b4d4/2e81c800-517a-11ec-b1ae-c1b029d25cc4/file-1kwlekg3l.jpeg\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 1st September Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 87 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 1st September Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kwlekg3k/dba4a1f6-c0be-4b58-b7b5-9b523266b4d4/2e81c800-517a-11ec-b1ae-c1b029d25cc4/file-1kwlekg3l.jpeg?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-mass-m-slides-on-the-wooden-wedge-which-in-turn-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-ehwmw1x5d7x3iyxu\"},{\"i\":103,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"An object of mass 'm' is being moved with a constant velocity under the action of an applied force of 2N along a frictionless surface with following surface profile. The correct applied force vs distance graph will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">76</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">An object of mass 'm' is being moved with a constant velocity under the action of an applied force of 2N along a frictionless surface with following surface profile.<br><br><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kwor5rmw/daec49f9-ff32-4882-91d4-493276fac000/c6e8ba80-5351-11ec-9cbb-695a838b20fb/file-1kwor5rmx.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kwor5rmw/daec49f9-ff32-4882-91d4-493276fac000/c6e8ba80-5351-11ec-9cbb-695a838b20fb/file-1kwor5rmx.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 1st September Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 86 English\\\"><br>The correct applied force vs distance graph will be :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 1st September Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kwor5rmw/daec49f9-ff32-4882-91d4-493276fac000/c6e8ba80-5351-11ec-9cbb-695a838b20fb/file-1kwor5rmx.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/an-object-of-mass-m-is-being-moved-with-a-constant-velocit-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-h1rmj7hfopx1hvm7\"},{\"i\":104,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Statement : 1 If three forces $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1},{\\\\overrightarrow F _2}$$ and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$ are represented by three sides of a triangle and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1} + {\\\\overrightarrow F _2} = - {\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$, then these three forces are concurrent forces and satisfy the condition for equilibrium. Statement : 2 A triangle made up of three forces $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1}$$, $${\\\\overrightarrow F _2}$$ and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$ as its sides taken in the same order, satisfy the condition for translatory equilibrium. In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">77</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Statement : 1<br><br>If three forces $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1},{\\\\overrightarrow F _2}$$ and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$ are represented by three sides of a triangle and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1} + {\\\\overrightarrow F _2} =  - {\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$, then these three forces are concurrent forces and satisfy the condition for equilibrium.<br><br>Statement : 2<br><br>A triangle made up of three forces $${\\\\overrightarrow F _1}$$, $${\\\\overrightarrow F _2}$$ and $${\\\\overrightarrow F _3}$$ as its sides taken in the same order, satisfy the condition for translatory equilibrium.<br><br>In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 31st August Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/statement--1brbrif-three-forces-overrightarrow-f-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-b7bjafg6ipnut5yh\"},{\"i\":105,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"The boxes of masse 2 kg and 8 kg are connected by a massless string passing over smooth pulleys. Calculate the time taken by box of mass 8 kg to strike the ground starting from rest. (use g = 10 m/s2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">78</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">The boxes of masse 2 kg and 8 kg are connected by a massless string passing over smooth pulleys. Calculate the time taken by box of mass 8 kg to strike the ground starting from rest. (use g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>)<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktqs87ux/4ab6260d-6280-4821-9eb8-b3756206cfea/df59bb90-190a-11ec-9e1c-4f8f7e7dad5b/file-1ktqs87uy.jpeg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 27th August Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 91 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 27th August Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktqs87ux/4ab6260d-6280-4821-9eb8-b3756206cfea/df59bb90-190a-11ec-9e1c-4f8f7e7dad5b/file-1ktqs87uy.jpeg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/the-boxes-of-masse-2-kg-and-8-kg-are-connected-by-a-massless-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-hxxrjt9juqsuaxwg\"},{\"i\":106,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"The initial mass of a rocket is 1000 kg. Calculate at what rate the fuel should be burnt so that the rocket is given an acceleration of 20 ms-2. The gases come out at a relative speed of 500 ms$$-$$1 with respect to the rocket : [Use g = 10 m/s2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">79</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">The initial mass of a rocket is 1000 kg. Calculate at what rate the fuel should be burnt so that the rocket is given an acceleration of 20 ms<sup>-2</sup>. The gases come out at a relative speed of 500 ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup> with respect to the rocket : [Use g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>]</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/the-initial-mass-of-a-rocket-is-1000-kg-calculate-at-what-r-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-mxkggeeuyzlwe46g\"},{\"i\":107,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A particle of mass M originally at rest is subjected to a force whose direction is constant but magnitude varies with time according to the relation $$F = {F_0}\\\\left[ {1 - {{\\\\left( {{{t - T} \\\\over T}} \\\\right)}^2}} \\\\right]$$ Where F0 and T are constants. The force acts only for the time interval 2T. The velocity v of the particle after time 2T is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">80</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle of mass M originally at rest is subjected to a force whose direction is constant but magnitude varies with time according to the relation <br><br>$$F = {F_0}\\\\left[ {1 - {{\\\\left( {{{t - T} \\\\over T}} \\\\right)}^2}} \\\\right]$$<br><br>Where F<sub>0</sub> and T are constants. The force acts only for the time interval 2T. The velocity v of the particle after time 2T is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 27th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-of-mass-m-originally-at-rest-is-subjected-to-a-fo-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-s6tbnewyvdmlrxmk\"},{\"i\":108,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A force $$\\\\overrightarrow F = (40\\\\widehat i + 10\\\\widehat j)N$$ acts on a body of mass 5 kg. If the body starts from rest, its position vector $$\\\\overrightarrow r $$ at time t = 10 s, will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">81</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A force $$\\\\overrightarrow F  = (40\\\\widehat i + 10\\\\widehat j)N$$ acts on a body of mass 5 kg. If the body starts from rest, its position vector $$\\\\overrightarrow r $$ at time t = 10 s, will be :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 25th July Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-force-overrightarrow-f--40widehat-i--10widehat-j-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-qbsc1tldbrr5btcb\"},{\"i\":109,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A steel block of 10 kg rests on a horizontal floor as shown. When three iron cylinders are placed on it as shown, the block and cylinders go down with an acceleration 0.2 m/s2. The normal reaction R' by the floor if mass of the iron cylinders are equal and of 20 kg each, is ____________ N. [Take g = 10 m/s2 and $$\\\\mu$$s = 0.2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">82</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A steel block of 10 kg rests on a horizontal floor as shown. When three iron cylinders are placed on it as shown, the block and cylinders go down with an acceleration 0.2 m/s<sup>2</sup>. The normal reaction R' by the floor if mass of the iron cylinders are equal and of 20 kg each, is ____________ N. [Take g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup> and $$\\\\mu$$<sub>s</sub> = 0.2]<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq87j4j/dfdeaca9-e470-4ce1-ada1-8484fd8f065c/26e76e30-f124-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq87j4k.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 97 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq87j4j/dfdeaca9-e470-4ce1-ada1-8484fd8f065c/26e76e30-f124-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq87j4k.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-steel-block-of-10-kg-rests-on-a-horizontal-floor-as-shown-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-w5tyd7vko3huch9l\"},{\"i\":110,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Morning Shift\",\"text\":\"A block of mass m slides along a floor while a force of magnitude F is applied to it at an angle $$\\\\theta$$ as shown in figure. The coefficient of kinetic friction is $$\\\\mu$$k. then, the block's acceleration 'a' is given by : (g is acceleration due to gravity)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">83</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass m slides along a floor while a force of magnitude F is applied to it at an angle $$\\\\theta$$ as shown in figure. The coefficient of kinetic friction is $$\\\\mu$$<sub>k</sub>. then, the block's acceleration 'a' is given by :<br><br>(g is acceleration due to gravity)<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmili649/c5367306-4ff7-43e9-84e6-062048ffac1d/cb587690-89f4-11eb-9c26-d9a423ffb060/file-1kmili64a.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 16th March Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 103 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 16th March Morning Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmili649/c5367306-4ff7-43e9-84e6-062048ffac1d/cb587690-89f4-11eb-9c26-d9a423ffb060/file-1kmili64a.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-mass-m-slides-along-a-floor-while-a-force-of-magn-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-w8ncndknfdvp7j8i\"},{\"i\":111,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"Two masses A and B, each of mass M are fixed together by a massless spring. A force acts on the mass B as shown in the figure. If the mass A starts moving away from mass B with acceleration 'a', then the acceleration of mass B will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">84</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two masses A and B, each of mass M are fixed together by a massless spring. A force acts on the mass B as shown in the figure. If the mass A starts moving away from mass B with acceleration 'a', then the acceleration of mass B will be :<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kluwg121/1d968e0f-fd73-4bcc-be1b-6cdb7c7f2fce/c4a6e490-7cec-11eb-8f7b-79760a5d8011/file-1kluwg122-248w.jpg\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Evening Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 104 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kluwg121/1d968e0f-fd73-4bcc-be1b-6cdb7c7f2fce/c4a6e490-7cec-11eb-8f7b-79760a5d8011/file-1kluwg122-248w.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-masses-a-and-b-each-of-mass-m-are-fixed-together-by-a-m-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-amxvrlxqchzw3twe\"},{\"i\":112,\"year\":2021,\"shift\":\"Evening Shift\",\"text\":\"A particle is projected with velocity v0 along x-axis. A damping force is acting on the particle which is proportional to the square of the distance from the origin i.e. ma = $$-$$ $$\\\\alpha$$x2. The distance at which the particle stops :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">85</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle is projected with velocity v<sub>0</sub> along x-axis. A damping force is acting on the particle which is proportional to the square of the distance from the origin i.e. ma = $$-$$ $$\\\\alpha$$x<sup>2</sup>. The distance at which the particle stops :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2021 (Online) 24th February Evening Shift</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-is-projected-with-velocity-vsub0sub-along-x-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-x6zyv1oyizwbuz7n\"},{\"i\":113,\"year\":2020,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A particle moving in the xy plane experiences a velocity dependent force $$\\\\overrightarrow F = k\\\\left( {{v_y}\\\\widehat i + {v_x}\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$ , where vx and vy are the x and y components of its velocity $$\\\\overrightarrow v $$ . If $$\\\\overrightarrow a $$ is the acceleration of the particle, then which of the following statements is true for the particle?\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">86</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle moving in the xy plane experiences a velocity dependent force\\n<br>$$\\\\overrightarrow F  = k\\\\left( {{v_y}\\\\widehat i + {v_x}\\\\widehat j} \\\\right)$$\\n, where v<sub>x</sub>\\nand v<sub>y</sub>\\n are the <br>x and y components of its velocity $$\\\\overrightarrow v $$\\n. If $$\\\\overrightarrow a $$\\n is the<br> acceleration of the particle, then\\n<br>which of the following statements is true for the particle?</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2020 (Online) 6th September Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-moving-in-the-xy-plane-experiences-a-velocity-dep-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-nuy3bny4wscxalh8\"},{\"i\":114,\"year\":2020,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"An insect is at the bottom of a hemispherical ditch of radius 1 m. It crawls up the ditch but starts slipping after it is at height h from the bottom. If the coefficient of friction between the ground and the insect is 0.75, then h is : (g = 10 ms–2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">87</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">An insect is at the bottom of a hemispherical ditch of radius 1 m. It crawls up the ditch but starts\\nslipping after it is at height h from the bottom. If the coefficient of friction between the ground and\\nthe insect is 0.75, then h is : \\n<br>(g = 10 ms<sup>–2</sup>)</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2020 (Online) 6th September Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/an-insect-is-at-the-bottom-of-a-hemispherical-ditch-of-radiu-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-6ufis0nzc5ez34ba\"},{\"i\":115,\"year\":2020,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A spaceship in space sweeps stationary interplanetary dust. As a result, its mass increases at a rate $${{dM\\\\left( t \\\\right)} \\\\over {dt}}$$ = bv2(t), where v(t) is its instantaneous velocity. The instantaneous acceleration of the satellite is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">88</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A spaceship in space sweeps stationary\\ninterplanetary dust. As a result, its mass\\n<br>increases at a rate $${{dM\\\\left( t \\\\right)} \\\\over {dt}}$$ = bv<sup>2</sup>(t), where v(t) is\\nits instantaneous velocity. The instantaneous\\nacceleration of the satellite is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2020 (Online) 5th September Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-spaceship-in-space-sweeps-stationary-interplanetary-dust-jee-main-physics-motion-blicv3twpolctgnl\"},{\"i\":116,\"year\":2020,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A small ball of mass m is thrown upward with velocity u from the ground. The ball experiences a resistive force mkv2 where v is its speed. The maximum height attained by the ball is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">89</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A small ball of mass m is thrown upward with velocity u from the ground. The ball experiences a\\nresistive force mkv<sup>2</sup>\\n where v is its speed. The maximum height attained by the ball is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2020 (Online) 4th September Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-small-ball-of-mass-m-is-thrown-upward-with-velocity-u-from-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-kmftbfkgfregnfrk\"},{\"i\":117,\"year\":2020,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A mass of 10 kg is suspended by a rope of length 4 m, from the ceiling. A force F is applied horizontally at the mid point of the rope such that the top half of the rope makes an angle of 45o with the vertical. Then F equal : (Take g = 10 ms–2 and the rope to be massless)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">90</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A mass of 10 kg is suspended by a rope of length 4 m, from the ceiling. A force F is applied\\nhorizontally at the mid point of the rope such that the top half of the rope makes an angle of 45<sup>o</sup>\\nwith the vertical. Then F equal : (Take g = 10 ms<sup>–2</sup> and the rope to be massless)</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2020 (Online) 7th January Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-mass-of-10-kg-is-suspended-by-a-rope-of-length-4-m-from-t-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-gkf50dw3aihatxzd\"},{\"i\":118,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A spring whose unstretched length is l has a force constant k. The spring is cut into two pieces of unstretched lengths l1 and l2 where, l1 = nl2 and n is an integer. The ratio k1/k2 of the corresponding force constant, k1 and k2 will be :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">91</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A spring whose unstretched length is l has a force constant k. The spring is cut into two pieces of unstretched\\nlengths l<sub>1</sub> and l<sub>2</sub> where, l<sub>1</sub> = nl<sub>2</sub> and n is an integer. The ratio k<sub>1</sub>/k<sub>2</sub> of the corresponding force constant, k<sub>1</sub> and\\nk<sub>2</sub> will be :\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th April Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-spring-whose-unstretched-length-is-l-has-a-force-constant-jee-main-physics-work-power-and-energy-xi1alq9jwsfpjxqt\"},{\"i\":119,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 5 kg is (i) pushed in case (A) and (ii) pulled in case (B), by a force F = 20 N, making an angle of 30o with the horizontal, as shown in the figures. The coefficient of friction between the block and floor is $$\\\\mu $$ = 0.2. The difference between the accelerations of the blocks, in case (B) and case (A) will be : (g = 10 ms–2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">92</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass 5 kg is (i) pushed in case (A) and (ii) pulled in case (B), by a force F = 20 N, making an\\nangle of 30<sup>o</sup> with the horizontal, as shown in the figures. The coefficient of friction between the block and\\nfloor is $$\\\\mu $$ = 0.2. The difference between the accelerations of the blocks, in case (B) and case (A) will be :\\n(g = 10 ms<sup>–2</sup>) \\n<img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf762wkjxv35uis/673373d6-5b77-484e-8976-3aeb901f828b/d852a840-a1e1-11e9-902e-23ffedc9804e/file-jf762wkjxv35uit.png\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th April Evening Slot Physics - Laws of Motion Question 117 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th April Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf762wkjxv35uis/673373d6-5b77-484e-8976-3aeb901f828b/d852a840-a1e1-11e9-902e-23ffedc9804e/file-jf762wkjxv35uit.png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-mass-5-kg-is-i-pushed-in-case-a-and-ii-pull-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-r4nqerfd5erq4mxp\"},{\"i\":120,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Two blocks A and B of masses mA = 1 kg and mB = 3 kg are kept on the table as shown in figure. The coefficient of friction between A and B is 0.2 and between B and the surface of the table is also 0.2. The maximum force F that can be applied on B horizontally, so that the block A does not slide over the block B is : [Take g = 10 m/s2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">93</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two blocks A and B of masses m<sub>A </sub>= 1 kg and m<sub>B </sub>= 3 kg are kept on the table as shown in figure. The coefficient of friction between A and B is 0.2 and between B and the surface of the table is also 0.2. The maximum force F that can be applied on B horizontally, so that the block A does not slide over the block B is :\\n<br> [Take g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>]\\n<img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/3rsa0w2w9jwzjluo5/a529b6a2-5f20-4153-81dc-10654e39e3e0/12ab8260-9089-11e9-86c1-73f7f991b766/file-3rsa0w2w9jwzjluo6.png\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Evening Slot Physics - Laws of Motion Question 118 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/3rsa0w2w9jwzjluo5/a529b6a2-5f20-4153-81dc-10654e39e3e0/12ab8260-9089-11e9-86c1-73f7f991b766/file-3rsa0w2w9jwzjluo6.png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-blocks-a-and-b-of-masses-msuba-sub-1-kg-and-msub-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-prtyyww5592iqyfk\"},{\"i\":121,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A bullet of mass 20 g has an initial speed of 1 ms–1 , just before it starts penetrating a mud wall of thickness 20 cm. If the wall offers a mean resistance of 2.5 × 10–2 N, the speed of the bullet after emerging from the other side of the wall is close to :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">94</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A bullet of mass 20 g has an initial speed of 1 ms<sup>–1</sup>\\n, just before it starts penetrating a mud wall of thickness\\n20 cm. If the wall offers a mean resistance of 2.5 × 10<sup>–2</sup> N, the speed of the bullet after emerging from the\\nother side of the wall is close to : </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-bullet-of-mass-20-g-has-an-initial-speed-of-1-mssup1s-jee-main-physics-laws-of-motion-zpliyadyiasbuegu\"},{\"i\":122,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A ball is thrown upward with an initial velocity V0 from the surface of the earth. The motion of the ball is affected by a drag force equal to m$$\\\\gamma $$u2 (where m is mass of the ball, u is its instantaneous velocity and $$\\\\gamma $$ is a constant). Time taken by the ball to rise to its zenith is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">95</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A ball is thrown upward with an initial velocity\\nV<sub>0</sub> from the surface of the earth. The motion\\nof the ball is affected by a drag force equal to\\nm$$\\\\gamma $$u<sup>2</sup> (where m is mass of the ball, u is its\\ninstantaneous velocity and $$\\\\gamma $$ is a constant).\\nTime taken by the ball to rise to its zenith is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-ball-is-thrown-upward-with-an-initial-velocity-vsub0su-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-jvsn9fkqrti2oj4c\"},{\"i\":123,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block kept on a rough inclined plane, as shown in the figure, remains at rest upto a maximum force 2 N down the inclined plane. The maximum external force up the inclined plane that does not move the block is 10 N. The coefficient of static friction between the block and the plane is : [Take g = 10 m/s2]\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">96</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block kept on a rough inclined plane, as shown in the figure, remains at rest upto a maximum force 2 N down the inclined plane. The maximum external force up the inclined plane that does not move the block is 10 N. The coefficient of static friction between the block and the plane is : [Take g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>] \\n<br><br><img src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/3ApkfDOiLxgeyfZt2/smVLBPy2WVgEPKz914lnk3UHJJBuN/ZUfu4xKmnxP8doJAWifUSJ/image.png\\\" style=\\\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Evening Slot Physics - Laws of Motion Question 121 English\\\">\\n</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/3ApkfDOiLxgeyfZt2/smVLBPy2WVgEPKz914lnk3UHJJBuN/ZUfu4xKmnxP8doJAWifUSJ/image.png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-kept-on-a-rough-inclined-plane-as-shown-in-the-figu-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-d4p0qmlq7lwsdia7\"},{\"i\":124,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Two forces P and Q, of magnitude 2F and 3F, respectively, are at an angle $$\\\\theta $$ with each other. If the force Q is doubled, then their resultant also gets doubled. Then, the angle $$\\\\theta $$ is -\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">97</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two forces P and Q, of magnitude 2F and 3F, respectively, are at an angle $$\\\\theta $$ with each other. If the force Q is doubled, then their resultant also gets doubled. Then, the angle $$\\\\theta $$ is -</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th January Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-forces-p-and-q-of-magnitude-2f-and-3f-respectively-ar-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-xtvvcphrfslt0wf3\"},{\"i\":125,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A mass of 10 kg is suspended vertically by a rope from the roof. When a horizontal force is applied on the rope at some point. the rope deviated at an angle of 45o at the roof point. If the suspended mass is at equilibrium, the magnitude of the force applied is (g = 10 ms$$-$$2\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">98</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A mass of 10 kg is suspended vertically by a rope from the roof. When a horizontal force is applied on the rope at some point. the rope deviated at an angle of 45<sup>o</sup> at the roof point. If the suspended mass is at equilibrium, the magnitude of the force applied is (g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 9th January Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-mass-of-10-kg-is-suspended-vertically-by-a-rope-from-the-r-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-fg4qq8kmcxtcrkxb\"},{\"i\":126,\"year\":2019,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block of mass 10 kg is kept on a rough inclined plane as shown in the figure. A force of 3 N is applied on the block. The coefficient of static friction between the plane and the block is 0.6. What should be the minimum value of force P, such that the block does not move downward? (take g = 10 ms$$-$$2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">99</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass 10 kg is kept on a rough inclined plane as shown in the figure. A force of 3 N is applied on the block. The coefficient of static friction between the plane and the block is 0.6. What should be the minimum value of force P, such that the block does not move downward? (take g = 10 ms<sup>$$-$$2</sup>)\\n<br><br><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8mglm7r/56c61599-5833-4a07-a2d9-19c58ae14fd2/827edc70-3fa1-11ed-835d-8b6c97a43374/file-1l8mglm7s.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8mglm7r/56c61599-5833-4a07-a2d9-19c58ae14fd2/827edc70-3fa1-11ed-835d-8b6c97a43374/file-1l8mglm7s.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 9th January Morning Slot Physics - Laws of Motion Question 124 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2019 (Online) 9th January Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8mglm7r/56c61599-5833-4a07-a2d9-19c58ae14fd2/827edc70-3fa1-11ed-835d-8b6c97a43374/file-1l8mglm7s.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/determine-minimum-value-of-force-f-required-to-keep-block-in-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-sobzdpcwretiaww1\"},{\"i\":127,\"year\":2018,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Two masses m1 = 5 kg and m2 = 10 kg, connected by an inextensible string over a frictionless pulley, are moving as shown in the figure. The coefficient of friction of horizontal surface is 0.15. The minimum weight m that should be put on top of m2 to stop the motion is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">100</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two masses m<sub>1</sub> = 5 kg and m<sub>2</sub> = 10 kg, connected by an inextensible\\nstring over a frictionless pulley, are moving as shown in the figure. The\\ncoefficient of friction of horizontal surface is 0.15. The minimum\\nweight m that should be put on top of m<sub>2</sub> to stop the motion is : \\n<img class=\\\"question-image\\\" src=\\\"https://gateclass.static.cdn.examgoal.net/QnesxWEJnmYijVnQK/eCK8N08Mme9lQl9W1twbQNO9fdQ5g/cLWLtQMyXwjU7k70O7FH4K/uploadfile.jpg\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2018 (Offline) Physics - Laws of Motion Question 130 English\\\"></div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2018 (Offline)</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://gateclass.static.cdn.examgoal.net/QnesxWEJnmYijVnQK/eCK8N08Mme9lQl9W1twbQNO9fdQ5g/cLWLtQMyXwjU7k70O7FH4K/uploadfile.jpg\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-masses-m1-5-kg-and-m2-10-kg-connected-by-an-inexten-2018-marks-4-26hup9owkhgkc37c.htm\"},{\"i\":128,\"year\":2018,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A body of mass 2 kg slides down with an acceleration of 3 m/s2 on a rough inclined plane having a slope of $${30^o}$$. The external force required to take the same body up the plane with the same acceleration will be : (g = 10 m/s2)\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">101</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A body of mass 2 kg slides down with an acceleration of 3 m/s<sup>2</sup> on a rough inclined plane having a slope of $${30^o}$$. The external force required to take the same body up the plane with the same acceleration will be : (g = 10 m/s<sup>2</sup>)</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2018 (Online) 15th April Evening Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-body-of-mass-2-kg-slides-down-with-an-acceleration-of-3-m-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-raxi3tx6mups4bm3\"},{\"i\":129,\"year\":2018,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A given object takes n times more time to slide down a $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ rough inclined plane as it takes to slide down a perfectly smooth $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ incline. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the object and the incline is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">102</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A given object takes n times more time to slide down a $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ rough inclined plane as it takes to slide down a perfectly smooth $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ incline. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the object and the incline is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2018 (Online) 15th April Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-given-object-takes-n-times-more-time-to-slide-down-a-45-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-rxdp8lrkr78mxivq\"},{\"i\":130,\"year\":2016,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A particle of mass m is acted upon by a force F given by the empirical law F =$${R \\\\over {{t^2}}}\\\\,v\\\\left( t \\\\right).$$ If this law is to be tested experimentally by observing the motion starting from rest, the best way is to plot :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">103</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle of mass m is acted upon by a force F given by the empirical law\\nF =$${R \\\\over {{t^2}}}\\\\,v\\\\left( t \\\\right).$$   If this law is to be tested experimentally by observing the motion starting from rest, the best way is to plot :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2016 (Online) 10th April Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-of-mass-m-is-acted-upon-by-a-force-f-given-by-the-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-jlehhxldhq0s6epx\"},{\"i\":131,\"year\":2016,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A rocket is fired vertically from the earth with an acceleration of 2g, where g is the gravitational acceleration. On an inclined plane inside the rocket, making an angle $$\\\\theta $$ with the horizontal, a point object of mass m is kept. The minimum coefficient of friction $$\\\\mu $$min between the mass and the inclined surface such that the mass does not move is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">104</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A rocket is fired vertically from the earth with an acceleration of 2g, where g is the\\ngravitational acceleration. On an inclined plane inside the rocket, making an angle $$\\\\theta $$ with the horizontal, a point object of mass <i>m</i> is kept. The minimum coefficient of friction $$\\\\mu $$<sub>min</sub> between the mass and the inclined surface such that the mass does not move is :</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2016 (Online) 9th April Morning Slot</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-rocket-is-fired-vertically-from-the-earth-with-an-accelera-jee-main-physics-units-and-measurements-kuudlvkeb8solx1k\"},{\"i\":132,\"year\":2015,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Given in the figure are two blocks $$A$$ and $$B$$ of weight 20 N and 100 N, respectively. These are being pressed against a wall by a force $$F$$ as shown. If the coefficient of friction between the blocks is 0.1 and between block $$B$$ and the wall is 0.15, the frictional force applied by the wall on block $$B$$ is :\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">105</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\"><img src=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l91dzva8/32a61b53-56bd-4d0a-b3d8-bf03d4828714/152ee910-47d7-11ed-9a0e-8f7a98995d79/file-1l91dzva9.png?format=png\\\" data-orsrc=\\\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l91dzva8/32a61b53-56bd-4d0a-b3d8-bf03d4828714/152ee910-47d7-11ed-9a0e-8f7a98995d79/file-1l91dzva9.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" style=\\\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\\\" alt=\\\"JEE Main 2015 (Offline) Physics - Laws of Motion Question 131 English\\\"><br>Given in the figure are two blocks $$A$$ and $$B$$ of weight 20 N and 100 N, respectively. These are being pressed against a wall by a force $$F$$ as shown. If the coefficient of friction between the blocks is 0.1 and between block $$B$$ and the wall is 0.15, the frictional force applied by the wall on block $$B$$ is : </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2015 (Offline)</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l91dzva8/32a61b53-56bd-4d0a-b3d8-bf03d4828714/152ee910-47d7-11ed-9a0e-8f7a98995d79/file-1l91dzva9.png?format=png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/given-in-the-figure-are-two-blocks-a-and-b-of-weight-2015-marks-4-pnlit96qke6wkauq.htm\"},{\"i\":133,\"year\":2014,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $$m$$ is placed on a surface with a vertical cross section given by $$y = {{{x^3}} \\\\over 6}.$$ If the coefficient of friction is $$0.5,$$ the maximum height above the ground at which the block can be placed without slipping is:\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">106</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass $$m$$ is placed on a surface with a vertical cross section given by $$y = {{{x^3}} \\\\over 6}.$$ If the coefficient of friction is $$0.5,$$  the maximum height above the ground at which the block can be placed without slipping is:</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">JEE Main 2014 (Offline)</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-mass-m-is-placed-on-a-surface-with-a-vertical-2014-marks-4-bddvgw1uyyt66w17.htm\"},{\"i\":134,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A particle of mass $$m$$ is at rest at the origin at time $$t=0.$$ It is subjected to a force $$F\\\\left( t \\\\right) = {F_0}{e^{ - bt}}$$ in the $$x$$ direction. Its speed $$v(t)$$ is depicted by which of the following curves? AIEEE 2012\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">107</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle of mass $$m$$ is at rest at the origin at time $$t=0.$$ It is subjected to a force $$F\\\\left( t \\\\right) = {F_0}{e^{ - bt}}$$ in the $$x$$ direction. Its speed $$v(t)$$ is depicted by which of the following curves? </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2012</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-of-mass-m-is-at-rest-at-the-origin-at-time-2010-marks-4-owqjhbeopuptncck.htm\"},{\"i\":135,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Two fixed frictionless inclined planes making an angle $${30^ \\\\circ }$$ and $${60^ \\\\circ }$$ with the vertical are shown in the figure. Two blocks $$A$$ and $$B$$ are placed on the two planes. What is the relative vertical acceleration of $$A$$ with respect to $$B$$ ? AIEEE 2010\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">108</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Two fixed frictionless inclined planes making an angle $${30^ \\\\circ }$$ and $${60^ \\\\circ }$$ with the vertical are shown in the figure. Two blocks $$A$$ and $$B$$ are placed on the two planes. What is the relative  vertical acceleration of $$A$$ with respect to $$B$$ ?\\n<img class=\\\"question-image\\\" src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/rjR3uE1VGxIU1BEwo/lHh0czqJjJhl4SPkoxl7ViuUUU1hr/17twO226UtQcF9EuTYKXj5/image.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"AIEEE 2010 Physics - Laws of Motion Question 132 English\\\"> </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2010</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/rjR3uE1VGxIU1BEwo/lHh0czqJjJhl4SPkoxl7ViuUUU1hr/17twO226UtQcF9EuTYKXj5/image.png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/two-fixed-frictionless-inclined-planes-making-an-angle-30-2010-marks-4-nsnoxfb1o8rlp9u3.htm\"},{\"i\":136,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block of mass $$m$$ is connected to another block of $$mass$$ $$M$$ by a spring (massless) of spring constant $$k.$$ The block are kept on a smooth horizontal plane. Initially the blocks are at rest and the spring is unstretched. Then a constant force $$F$$ starts acting on the block of mass $$M$$ to pull it. Find the force of the block of mass $$m.$$ AIEEE 2007\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">109</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block of mass $$m$$ is connected to another block of $$mass$$ $$M$$ by a spring (massless) of spring constant $$k.$$ The block are kept on a smooth horizontal plane. Initially the blocks are at rest and the spring is unstretched. Then a constant force $$F$$  starts acting on the block of mass $$M$$ to pull it. Find the force of the block of mass $$m.$$ </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2007</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-of-mass-m-is-connected-to-another-block-of-mas-2007-marks-4-zdwyrk0wses0l84x.htm\"},{\"i\":137,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A smooth block is released at rest on a $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ incline and then slides a distance $$'d'$$. The time taken to slide is $$'n'$$ times as much to slide on rough incline than on a smooth incline. The coefficient of friction is AIEEE 2005\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">110</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A smooth block is released at rest on a $${45^ \\\\circ }$$ incline and then slides a distance $$'d'$$. The time taken to slide is $$'n'$$ times as much to slide on rough incline than on a smooth incline. The coefficient of friction is </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2005</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-smooth-block-is-released-at-rest-on-a-45-circ-inc-2005-marks-4-rtt5xb5de04azlez.htm\"},{\"i\":138,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A particle of mass 0.3 kg subjected to a force $$F=-kx$$ with $$k=15$$ $$N/m$$. What will be its initial acceleration if it is released from a point 20 cm away from the origin? AIEEE 2005\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">111</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A particle of mass 0.3 kg subjected to a force $$F=-kx$$ with $$k=15$$ $$N/m$$. What will be its initial acceleration if it is released from a point 20 cm away from the origin?</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2005</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-particle-of-mass-03-kg-subjected-to-a-force-f-2005-marks-4-9zfe7ponnmru4a6x.htm\"},{\"i\":139,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"A block is kept on a frictionless inclined surface with angle of inclination $$'\\\\,\\\\alpha \\\\,'.$$ The incline is given an acceleration $$a$$ to keep the block stationary. Then $$a$$ is equal to AIEEE 2005\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">112</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">A block is kept on a frictionless inclined surface with angle of inclination $$'\\\\,\\\\alpha \\\\,'.$$ The incline is given an acceleration $$a$$ to keep the block stationary. Then $$a$$ is equal to \\n<img class=\\\"question-image\\\" src=\\\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/bKJx18YMzAYlbtd8y/UDSaBl3VxDJ9gJeMNlo99tEhkhpNo/eZJsUomsswTmHUtAzphlWk/image.png\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\" alt=\\\"AIEEE 2005 Physics - Laws of Motion Question 133 English\\\"> </div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIEEE 2005</div></div></div>\",\"opts\":[],\"imgs\":[\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/bKJx18YMzAYlbtd8y/UDSaBl3VxDJ9gJeMNlo99tEhkhpNo/eZJsUomsswTmHUtAzphlWk/image.png\"],\"href\":\"/past-years/jee/question/a-block-is-kept-on-a-frictionless-inclined-surface-with-angl-2005-marks-4-pxvqrres34zsmijz.htm\"},{\"i\":140,\"year\":0,\"shift\":\"\",\"text\":\"Consider a car moving on a straight road with a speed of $$100$$ $$m/s$$. The distance at which car can be stopped is $$\\\\left[ {{\\\\mu _k} = 0.5} \\\\right]$$ AIEEE 2005\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"bg-blue-500 text-white self-start w-[25px] h-[25px] shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center rounded-[50%] text-[80%]\\\">113</div> <div class=\\\"flex flex-col gap-2 lg:gap-4\\\"><div class=\\\"opacity-80 overflow-hidden min-w-0\\\" style=\\\"max-height: 140px\\\">Consider a car moving on a straight road with a speed of $$100$$ $$m/s$$. The distance at which car can be stopped is $$\\\\left[ {{\\\\mu _k} = 0.5} \\\\right]$$</div> <div class=\\\"flex gap-2\\\"><div class=\\\"text-sm bg-green-500 text-green-500 bg-opacity-10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded\\\">AIE